var book = {
	"name": "2 Kings",
	"numChapters": 25,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9535A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9535A\"></sup>Moab rebelled against Israel after the death of Ahab.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Ahaziah fell through the lattice in his upper chamber which <i>was</i> in Samaria, and became ill. So he sent messengers and said to them, “Go, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9536B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9536B\"></sup>inquire of Baal-zebub, the god of Ekron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9536C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9536C\"></sup>whether I will recover from this sickness.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9537D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9537D\"></sup>Elijah the Tishbite, “Arise, go up to meet the messengers of the king of Samaria and say to them, ‘Is it because there is no God in Israel <i>that</i> you are going to inquire of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9537E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9537E\"></sup>Baal-zebub, the god of Ekron?’",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now therefore thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9538F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9538F\"></sup>You shall not come down from the bed where you have gone up, but you shall surely die.’” Then Elijah departed.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When the messengers returned to him he said to them, “Why have you returned?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They said to him, “A man came up to meet us and said to us, ‘Go, return to the king who sent you and say to him, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Is it because there is no God in Israel <i>that</i> you are sending <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9540G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9540G\"></sup>to inquire of Baal-zebub, the god of Ekron? Therefore you shall not come down from the bed where you have gone up, but shall surely die.’”’”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He said to them, “What kind of man was he who came up to meet you and spoke these words to you?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They answered him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9542H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9542H\"></sup><i>He was</i> a hairy man with a leather girdle bound about his loins.” And he said, “It is Elijah the Tishbite.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then <i>the king</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9543I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9543I\"></sup>sent to him a captain of fifty with his fifty. And he went up to him, and behold, he was sitting on the top of the hill. And he said to him, “O man of God, the king says, ‘Come down.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Elijah replied to the captain of fifty, “If I am a man of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9544J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9544J\"></sup>let fire come down from heaven and consume you and your fifty.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9544K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9544K\"></sup>Then fire came down from heaven and consumed him and his fifty.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So he again sent to him another captain of fifty with his fifty. And he said to him, “O man of God, thus says the king, ‘Come down quickly.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Elijah replied to them, “If I am a man of God, let fire come down from heaven and consume you and your fifty.” Then the fire of God came down from heaven and consumed him and his fifty.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9547L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9547L\"></sup>again sent the captain of a third fifty with his fifty. When the third captain of fifty went up, he came and bowed down on his knees before Elijah, and begged him and said to him, “O man of God, please let my life and the lives of these fifty servants of yours be precious in your sight.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Behold fire came down from heaven and consumed the first two captains of fifty with their fifties; but now let my life be precious in your sight.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9549M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9549M\"></sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Elijah, “Go down with him; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9549N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9549N\"></sup>do not be afraid of him.” So he arose and went down with him to the king.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then he said to him, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Because you have sent messengers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9550O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9550O\"></sup>to inquire of Baal-zebub, the god of Ekron—is it because there is no God in Israel to inquire of His word?—therefore you shall not come down from the bed where you have gone up, but shall surely die.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So Ahaziah died according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which Elijah had spoken. And because he had no son, Jehoram became king in his place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9551P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9551P\"></sup>in the second year of Jehoram the son of Jehoshaphat, king of Judah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Ahaziah which he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>And it came about when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was about to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9553A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9553A\"></sup>take up Elijah by a whirlwind to heaven, that Elijah went with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9553B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9553B\"></sup>Elisha from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9553C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9553C\"></sup>Gilgal.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Elijah said to Elisha, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9554D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9554D\"></sup>Stay here please, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sent me as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9554E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9554E\"></sup>Bethel.” But Elisha said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9554F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9554F\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives and as you yourself live, I will not leave you.” So they went down to Bethel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9555G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9555G\"></sup>the sons of the prophets who <i>were at</i> Bethel came out to Elisha and said to him, “Do you know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will take away your master from over you today?” And he said, “Yes, I know; be still.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Elijah said to him, “Elisha, please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9556H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9556H\"></sup>stay here, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sent me to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9556I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9556I\"></sup>Jericho.” But he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9556J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9556J\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, and as you yourself live, I will not leave you.” So they came to Jericho.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9557K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9557K\"></sup>The sons of the prophets who <i>were</i> at Jericho approached Elisha and said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9557L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9557L\"></sup>Do you know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will take away your master from over you today?” And he answered, “Yes, I know; be still.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Elijah said to him, “Please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9558M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9558M\"></sup>stay here, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sent me to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9558N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9558N\"></sup>the Jordan.” And he said, “As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, and as you yourself live, I will not leave you.” So the two of them went on.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9559O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9559O\"></sup>fifty men of the sons of the prophets went and stood opposite <i>them</i> at a distance, while the two of them stood by the Jordan.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Elijah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9560P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9560P\"></sup>took his mantle and folded it together and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9560Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9560Q\"></sup>struck the waters, and they were divided here and there, so that the two of them crossed over on dry ground.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When they had crossed over, Elijah said to Elisha, “Ask what I shall do for you before I am taken from you.” And Elisha said, “Please, let a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9561R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9561R\"></sup>double portion of your spirit be upon me.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He said, “You have asked a hard thing. <i>Nevertheless</i>, if you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9562S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9562S\"></sup>see me when I am taken from you, it shall be so for you; but if not, it shall not be <i>so</i>.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As they were going along and talking, behold, <i>there appeared</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9563T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9563T\"></sup>a chariot of fire and horses of fire which separated the two of them. And Elijah went up by a whirlwind to heaven.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Elisha saw <i>it</i> and cried out, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9564U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9564U\"></sup>My father, my father, the chariots of Israel and its horsemen!” And he saw Elijah no more. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9564V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9564V\"></sup>he took hold of his own clothes and tore them in two pieces.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He also took up the mantle of Elijah that fell from him and returned and stood by the bank of the Jordan.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He took the mantle of Elijah that fell from him and struck the waters and said, “Where is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Elijah?” And when he also had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9566W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9566W\"></sup>struck the waters, they were divided here and there; and Elisha crossed over.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9567X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9567X\"></sup>the sons of the prophets who <i>were</i> at Jericho opposite <i>him</i> saw him, they said, “The spirit of Elijah rests on Elisha.” And they came to meet him and bowed themselves to the ground before him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They said to him, “Behold now, there are with your servants fifty strong men, please let them go and search for your master; perhaps <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9568Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9568Y\"></sup>the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has taken him up and cast him on some mountain or into some valley.” And he said, “You shall not send.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9569Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9569Z\"></sup>they urged him until he was ashamed, he said, “Send.” They sent therefore fifty men; and they searched three days but did not find him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They returned to him while he was staying at Jericho; and he said to them, “Did I not say to you, ‘Do not go’?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the men of the city said to Elisha, “Behold now, the situation of this city is pleasant, as my lord sees; but the water is bad and the land is unfruitful.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He said, “Bring me a new jar, and put salt in it.” So they brought <i>it</i> to him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He went out to the spring of water and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9573AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9573AA\"></sup>threw salt in it and said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘I have purified these waters; there shall not be from there death or unfruitfulness any longer.’”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So the waters have been purified to this day, according to the word of Elisha which he spoke.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then he went up from there to Bethel; and as he was going up by the way, young lads came out from the city and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9575AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9575AB\"></sup>mocked him and said to him, “Go up, you baldhead; go up, you baldhead!”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When he looked behind him and saw them, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9576AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9576AC\"></sup>cursed them in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Then two female bears came out of the woods and tore up forty-two lads of their number.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He went from there to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9577AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9577AD\"></sup>Mount Carmel, and from there he returned to Samaria."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Now Jehoram the son of Ahab became king over Israel at Samaria <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9578A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9578A\"></sup>in the eighteenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and reigned twelve years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, though not like his father and his mother; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9579B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9579B\"></sup>he put away the <i>sacred</i> pillar of Baal <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9579C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9579C\"></sup>which his father had made.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Nevertheless, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9580D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9580D\"></sup>he clung to the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9580E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9580E\"></sup>which he made Israel sin; he did not depart from them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now Mesha king of Moab was a sheep breeder, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9581F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9581F\"></sup>used to pay the king of Israel 100,000 lambs and the wool of 100,000 rams.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9582G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9582G\"></sup>when Ahab died, the king of Moab rebelled against the king of Israel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And King Jehoram went out of Samaria at that time and mustered all Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then he went and sent <i>word</i> to Jehoshaphat the king of Judah, saying, “The king of Moab has rebelled against me. Will you go with me to fight against Moab?” And he said, “I will go up; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9584H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9584H\"></sup>I am as you are, my people as your people, my horses as your horses.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He said, “Which way shall we go up?” And he answered, “The way of the wilderness of Edom.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9586I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9586I\"></sup>the king of Israel went with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9586J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9586J\"></sup>the king of Judah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9586K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9586K\"></sup>the king of Edom; and they made a circuit of seven days’ journey, and there was no water for the army or for the cattle that followed them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then the king of Israel said, “Alas! For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has called these three kings to give them into the hand of Moab.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Jehoshaphat said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9588L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9588L\"></sup>Is there not a prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> here, that we may inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by him?” And one of the king of Israel’s servants answered and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9588M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9588M\"></sup>Elisha the son of Shaphat is here, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9588N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9588N\"></sup>who used to pour water on the hands of Elijah.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Jehoshaphat said, “The word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with him.” So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat and the king of Edom went down to him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now Elisha said to the king of Israel, “What do I have to do with you? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9590O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9590O\"></sup>Go to the prophets of your father and to the prophets of your mother.” And the king of Israel said to him, “No, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has called these three kings <i>together</i> to give them into the hand of Moab.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Elisha said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9591P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9591P\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts lives, before whom I stand, were it not that I regard the presence of Jehoshaphat the king of Judah, I would not look at you nor see you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9592Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9592Q\"></sup>bring me a minstrel.” And it came about, when the minstrel played, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9592R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9592R\"></sup>the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came upon him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Make this valley full of trenches.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘You shall not see wind nor shall you see rain; yet that valley <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9594S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9594S\"></sup>shall be filled with water, so that you shall drink, both you and your cattle and your beasts.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>This is but a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9595T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9595T\"></sup>slight thing in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; He will also give the Moabites into your hand.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9596U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9596U\"></sup>Then you shall strike every fortified city and every choice city, and fell every good tree and stop all springs of water, and mar every good piece of land with stones.’”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>It happened in the morning <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9597V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9597V\"></sup>about the time of offering the sacrifice, that behold, water came by the way of Edom, and the country was filled with water.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Now all the Moabites heard that the kings had come up to fight against them. And all who were able to put on armor and older were summoned and stood on the border.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>They rose early in the morning, and the sun shone on the water, and the Moabites saw the water opposite <i>them</i> as red as blood.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then they said, “This is blood; the kings have surely fought together, and they have slain one another. Now therefore, Moab, to the spoil!”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But when they came to the camp of Israel, the Israelites arose and struck the Moabites, so that they fled before them; and they went forward into the land, slaughtering the Moabites.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9602W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9602W\"></sup>Thus they destroyed the cities; and each one threw a stone on every piece of good land and filled it. So they stopped all the springs of water and felled all the good trees, until in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9602X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9602X\"></sup>Kir-hareseth <i>only</i> they left its stones; however, the slingers went about <i>it</i> and struck it.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When the king of Moab saw that the battle was too fierce for him, he took with him 700 men who drew swords, to break through to the king of Edom; but they could not.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then he took his oldest son who was to reign in his place, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9604Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9604Y\"></sup>offered him as a burnt offering on the wall. And there came great wrath against Israel, and they departed from him and returned to their own land."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Now a certain woman of the wives of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9605A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9605A\"></sup>the sons of the prophets cried out to Elisha, “Your servant my husband is dead, and you know that your servant feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9605B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9605B\"></sup>the creditor has come to take my two children to be his slaves.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Elisha said to her, “What shall I do for you? Tell me, what do you have in the house?” And she said, “Your maidservant has nothing in the house except <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9606C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9606C\"></sup>a jar of oil.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then he said, “Go, borrow vessels at large for yourself from all your neighbors, <i>even</i> empty vessels; do not get a few.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And you shall go in and shut the door behind you and your sons, and pour out into all these vessels, and you shall set aside what is full.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So she went from him and shut the door behind her and her sons; they were bringing <i>the vessels</i> to her and she poured.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9610D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9610D\"></sup>the vessels were full, she said to her son, “Bring me another vessel.” And he said to her, “There is not one vessel more.” And the oil stopped.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then she came and told <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9611E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9611E\"></sup>the man of God. And he said, “Go, sell the oil and pay your debt, and you <i>and</i> your sons can live on the rest.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now there came a day when Elisha passed over to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9612F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9612F\"></sup>Shunem, where there was a prominent woman, and she persuaded him to eat food. And so it was, as often as he passed by, he turned in there to eat food.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>She said to her husband, “Behold now, I perceive that this is a holy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9613G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9613G\"></sup>man of God passing by us continually.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Please, let us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9614H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9614H\"></sup>make a little walled upper chamber and let us set a bed for him there, and a table and a chair and a lampstand; and it shall be, when he comes to us, <i>that</i> he can turn in there.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>One day he came there and turned in to the upper chamber and rested.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9616I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9616I\"></sup>Gehazi his servant, “Call this Shunammite.” And when he had called her, she stood before him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He said to him, “Say now to her, ‘Behold, you have been careful for us with all this care; what can I do for you? Would you be spoken for to the king or to the captain of the army?’” And she answered, “I live among my own people.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So he said, “What then is to be done for her?” And Gehazi answered, “Truly she has no son and her husband is old.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He said, “Call her.” When he had called her, she stood in the doorway.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9620J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9620J\"></sup>At this season next year you will embrace a son.” And she said, “No, my lord, O man of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9620K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9620K\"></sup>do not lie to your maidservant.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The woman conceived and bore a son at that season the next year, as Elisha had said to her.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When the child was grown, the day came that he went out to his father to the reapers.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He said to his father, “My head, my head.” And he said to his servant, “Carry him to his mother.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When he had taken him and brought him to his mother, he sat on her lap until noon, and <i>then</i> died.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>She went up and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9625L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9625L\"></sup>laid him on the bed of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9625M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9625M\"></sup>the man of God, and shut <i>the door</i> behind him and went out.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then she called to her husband and said, “Please send me one of the servants and one of the donkeys, that I may run to the man of God and return.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He said, “Why will you go to him today? It is neither <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9627N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9627N\"></sup>new moon nor sabbath.” And she said, “<i>It will be</i> well.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then she saddled a donkey and said to her servant, “Drive and go forward; do not slow down the pace for me unless I tell you.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So she went and came to the man of God to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9629O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9629O\"></sup>Mount Carmel.When the man of God saw her at a distance, he said to Gehazi his servant, “Behold, there is the Shunammite.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Please run now to meet her and say to her, ‘Is it well with you? Is it well with your husband? Is it well with the child?’” And she answered, “It is well.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When she came to the man of God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9631P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9631P\"></sup>to the hill, she caught hold of his feet. And Gehazi came near to push her away; but the man of God said, “Let her alone, for her soul is troubled within her; and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has hidden it from me and has not told me.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then she said, “Did I ask for a son from my lord? Did I not say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9632Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9632Q\"></sup>Do not deceive me’?”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then he said to Gehazi, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9633R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9633R\"></sup>Gird up your loins and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9633S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9633S\"></sup>take my staff in your hand, and go your way; if you meet any man, do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9633T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9633T\"></sup>salute him, and if anyone salutes you, do not answer him; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9633U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9633U\"></sup>lay my staff on the lad’s face.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The mother of the lad said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9634V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9634V\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives and as you yourself live, I will not leave you.” And he arose and followed her.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Gehazi passed on before them and laid the staff on the lad’s face, but there was no sound or response. So he returned to meet him and told him, “The lad <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9635W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9635W\"></sup>has not awakened.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>When Elisha came into the house, behold the lad was dead and laid on his bed.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So he entered and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9637X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9637X\"></sup>shut the door behind them both and prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9638Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9638Y\"></sup>he went up and lay on the child, and put his mouth on his mouth and his eyes on his eyes and his hands on his hands, and he stretched himself on him; and the flesh of the child became warm.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then he returned and walked in the house once back and forth, and went up and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9639Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9639Z\"></sup>stretched himself on him; and the lad sneezed seven times and the lad opened his eyes.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>He called Gehazi and said, “Call this Shunammite.” So he called her. And when she came in to him, he said, “Take up your son.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then she went in and fell at his feet and bowed herself to the ground, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9641AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9641AA\"></sup>she took up her son and went out.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>When Elisha returned to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9642AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9642AB\"></sup>Gilgal, <i>there was</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9642AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9642AC\"></sup>a famine in the land. As <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9642AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9642AD\"></sup>the sons of the prophets <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9642AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9642AE\"></sup>were sitting before him, he said to his servant, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9642AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9642AF\"></sup>Put on the large pot and boil stew for the sons of the prophets.”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Then one went out into the field to gather herbs, and found a wild vine and gathered from it his lap full of wild gourds, and came and sliced them into the pot of stew, for they did not know <i>what they were</i>.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>So they poured <i>it</i> out for the men to eat. And as they were eating of the stew, they cried out and said, “O man of God, there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9644AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9644AG\"></sup>death in the pot.” And they were unable to eat.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>But he said, “Now bring meal.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9645AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9645AH\"></sup>He threw it into the pot and said, “Pour <i>it</i> out for the people that they may eat.” Then there was no harm in the pot.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Now a man came from Baal-shalishah, and brought the man of God bread of the first fruits, twenty loaves of barley and fresh ears of grain in his sack. And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9646AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9646AI\"></sup>Give <i>them</i> to the people that they may eat.”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>His attendant said, “What, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9647AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9647AJ\"></sup>will I set this before a hundred men?” But he said, “Give <i>them</i> to the people that they may eat, for thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘They shall eat and have <i>some</i> left over.’”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>So he set <i>it</i> before them, and they ate and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9648AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9648AK\"></sup>had <i>some</i> left over, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9649A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9649A\"></sup>Naaman, captain of the army of the king of Aram, was a great man with his master, and highly respected, because by him the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given victory to Aram. The man was also a valiant warrior, <i>but he was</i> a leper.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now the Arameans had gone out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9650B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9650B\"></sup>in bands and had taken captive a little girl from the land of Israel; and she waited on Naaman’s wife.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>She said to her mistress, “I wish that my master were with the prophet who is in Samaria! Then he would cure him of his leprosy.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Naaman went in and told his master, saying, “Thus and thus spoke the girl who is from the land of Israel.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the king of Aram said, “Go now, and I will send a letter to the king of Israel.” He departed and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9653C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9653C\"></sup>took with him ten talents of silver and six thousand <i>shekels</i> of gold and ten <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9653D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9653D\"></sup>changes of clothes.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He brought the letter to the king of Israel, saying, “And now as this letter comes to you, behold, I have sent Naaman my servant to you, that you may cure him of his leprosy.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the king of Israel read the letter, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9655E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9655E\"></sup>he tore his clothes and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9655F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9655F\"></sup>Am I God, to kill and to make alive, that this man is sending <i>word</i> to me to cure a man of his leprosy? But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9655G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9655G\"></sup>consider now, and see how he is seeking a quarrel against me.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>It happened when Elisha <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9656H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9656H\"></sup>the man of God heard that the king of Israel had torn his clothes, that he sent <i>word</i> to the king, saying, “Why have you torn your clothes? Now let him come to me, and he shall know that there is a prophet in Israel.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Naaman came with his horses and his chariots and stood at the doorway of the house of Elisha.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Elisha sent a messenger to him, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9658I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9658I\"></sup>Go and wash in the Jordan seven times, and your flesh will be restored to you and <i>you will</i> be clean.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Naaman was furious and went away and said, “Behold, I thought, ‘He will surely come out to me and stand and call on the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, and wave his hand over the place and cure the leper.’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Are not Abanah and Pharpar, the rivers of Damascus, better than all the waters of Israel? Could I not wash in them and be clean?” So he turned and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9660J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9660J\"></sup>went away in a rage.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9661K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9661K\"></sup>Then his servants came near and spoke to him and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9661L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9661L\"></sup>My father, had the prophet told you <i>to do some</i> great thing, would you not have done <i>it</i>? How much more <i>then</i>, when he says to you, ‘Wash, and be clean’?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So he went down and dipped <i>himself</i> seven times in the Jordan, according to the word of the man of God; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9662M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9662M\"></sup>his flesh was restored like the flesh of a little child and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9662N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9662N\"></sup>he was clean.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When he returned to the man of God with all his company, and came and stood before him, he said, “Behold now, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9663O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9663O\"></sup>I know that there is no God in all the earth, but in Israel; so please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9663P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9663P\"></sup>take a present from your servant now.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9664Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9664Q\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, before whom I stand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9664R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9664R\"></sup>I will take nothing.” And he urged him to take <i>it</i>, but he refused.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Naaman said, “If not, please let your servant at least be given two mules’ load of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9665S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9665S\"></sup>earth; for your servant will no longer offer burnt offering nor will he sacrifice to other gods, but to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>In this matter may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> pardon your servant: when my master goes into the house of Rimmon to worship there, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9666T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9666T\"></sup>he leans on my hand and I bow myself in the house of Rimmon, when I bow myself in the house of Rimmon, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> pardon your servant in this matter.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9667U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9667U\"></sup>Go in peace.” So he departed from him some distance.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9668V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9668V\"></sup>Gehazi, the servant of Elisha the man of God, thought, “Behold, my master has spared this Naaman the Aramean, by not receiving from his hands what he brought. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9668W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9668W\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, I will run after him and take something from him.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So Gehazi pursued Naaman. When Naaman saw one running after him, he came down from the chariot to meet him and said, “Is all well?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9670X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9670X\"></sup>All is well. My master has sent me, saying, ‘Behold, just now two young men of the sons of the prophets have come to me from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9670Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9670Y\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim. Please give them a talent of silver and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9670Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9670Z\"></sup>two changes of clothes.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Naaman said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9671AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9671AA\"></sup>Be pleased to take two talents.” And he urged him, and bound two talents of silver in two bags with two changes of clothes and gave them to two of his servants; and they carried <i>them</i> before him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When he came to the hill, he took them from their hand and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9672AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9672AB\"></sup>deposited them in the house, and he sent the men away, and they departed.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But he went in and stood before his master. And Elisha said to him, “Where have you been, Gehazi?” And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9673AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9673AC\"></sup>Your servant went nowhere.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then he said to him, “Did not my heart go <i>with you</i>, when the man turned from his chariot to meet you? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9674AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9674AD\"></sup>Is it a time to receive money and to receive clothes and olive groves and vineyards and sheep and oxen and male and female servants?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Therefore, the leprosy of Naaman shall cling to you and to your descendants forever.” So he went out from his presence <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9675AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9675AE\"></sup>a leper <i>as white</i> as snow."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9676A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9676A\"></sup>the sons of the prophets said to Elisha, “Behold now, the place before you where we are living is too limited for us.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Please let us go to the Jordan and each of us take from there a beam, and let us make a place there for ourselves where we may live.” So he said, “Go.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then one said, “Please be willing to go with your servants.” And he answered, “I shall go.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So he went with them; and when they came to the Jordan, they cut down trees.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But as one was felling a beam, the axe head fell into the water; and he cried out and said, “Alas, my master! For it was borrowed.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the man of God said, “Where did it fall?” And when he showed him the place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9681B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9681B\"></sup>he cut off a stick and threw <i>it</i> in there, and made the iron float.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He said, “Take it up for yourself.” So he put out his hand and took it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now the king of Aram was warring against Israel; and he counseled with his servants saying, “In such and such a place shall be my camp.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9684C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9684C\"></sup>The man of God sent <i>word</i> to the king of Israel saying, “Beware that you do not pass this place, for the Arameans are coming down there.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The king of Israel sent to the place about which the man of God had told him; thus he warned him, so that he guarded himself there, more than once or twice.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now the heart of the king of Aram was enraged over this thing; and he called his servants and said to them, “Will you tell me which of us is for the king of Israel?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>One of his servants said, “No, my lord, O king; but Elisha, the prophet who is in Israel, tells the king of Israel the words that you speak in your bedroom.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So he said, “Go and see where he is, that I may send and take him.” And it was told him, saying, “Behold, he is in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9688D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9688D\"></sup>Dothan.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He sent horses and chariots and a great army there, and they came by night and surrounded the city.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now when the attendant of the man of God had risen early and gone out, behold, an army with horses and chariots was circling the city. And his servant said to him, “Alas, my master! What shall we do?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So he answered, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9691E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9691E\"></sup>Do not fear, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9691F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9691F\"></sup>those who are with us are more than those who are with them.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Elisha prayed and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9692G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9692G\"></sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I pray, open his eyes that he may see.” And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> opened the servant’s eyes and he saw; and behold, the mountain was full of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9692H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9692H\"></sup>horses and chariots of fire all around Elisha.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When they came down to him, Elisha prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “Strike this people with blindness, I pray.” So He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9693I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9693I\"></sup>struck them with blindness according to the word of Elisha.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Elisha said to them, “This is not the way, nor is this the city; follow me and I will bring you to the man whom you seek.” And he brought them to Samaria.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When they had come into Samaria, Elisha said, “O <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9695J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9695J\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, open the eyes of these <i>men</i>, that they may see.” So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> opened their eyes and they saw; and behold, they were in the midst of Samaria.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the king of Israel when he saw them, said to Elisha, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9696K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9696K\"></sup>My father, shall I kill them? Shall I kill them?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He answered, “You shall not kill <i>them</i>. Would you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9697L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9697L\"></sup>kill those you have taken captive with your sword and with your bow? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9697M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9697M\"></sup>Set bread and water before them, that they may eat and drink and go to their master.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So he prepared a great feast for them; and when they had eaten and drunk he sent them away, and they went to their master. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9698N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9698N\"></sup>the marauding bands of Arameans did not come again into the land of Israel.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now it came about after this, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9699O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9699O\"></sup>Ben-hadad king of Aram gathered all his army and went up and besieged Samaria.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>There was a great <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9700P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9700P\"></sup>famine in Samaria; and behold, they besieged it, until a donkey’s head was sold for eighty <i>shekels</i> of silver, and a fourth of a kab of dove’s dung for five <i>shekels</i> of silver.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>As the king of Israel was passing by on the wall a woman cried out to him, saying, “Help, my lord, O king!”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He said, “If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> does not help you, from where shall I help you? From the threshing floor, or from the wine press?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And the king said to her, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9703Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9703Q\"></sup>What is the matter with you?” And she answered, “This woman said to me, ‘Give your son that we may eat him today, and we will eat my son tomorrow.’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9704R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9704R\"></sup>So we boiled my son and ate him; and I said to her on the next day, ‘Give your son, that we may eat him’; but she has hidden her son.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When the king heard the words of the woman, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9705S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9705S\"></sup>he tore his clothes—now he was passing by on the wall—and the people looked, and behold, he had sackcloth beneath on his body.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then he said, “May <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9706T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9706T\"></sup>God do so to me and more also, if the head of Elisha the son of Shaphat remains on him today.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Now Elisha was sitting in his house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9707U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9707U\"></sup>the elders were sitting with him. And <i>the king</i> sent a man from his presence; but before the messenger came to him, he said to the elders, “Do you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9707V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9707V\"></sup>see how this son of a murderer has sent to take away my head? Look, when the messenger comes, shut the door and hold the door shut against him. Is not the sound of his master’s feet behind him?”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>While he was still talking with them, behold, the messenger came down to him and he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9708W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9708W\"></sup>Behold, this evil is from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; why should I wait for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> any longer?”"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>Then Elisha said, “Listen to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9709A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9709A\"></sup>Tomorrow about this time a measure of fine flour will be <i>sold</i> for a shekel, and two measures of barley for a shekel, in the gate of Samaria.’”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9710B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9710B\"></sup>The royal officer on whose hand the king was leaning answered the man of God and said, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9710C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9710C\"></sup>if the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> should make windows in heaven, could this thing be?” Then he said, “Behold, you will see it with your own eyes, but you will not eat of it.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now there were four <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9711D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9711D\"></sup>leprous men at the entrance of the gate; and they said to one another, “Why do we sit here until we die?",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If we say, ‘We will enter the city,’ then the famine is in the city and we will die there; and if we sit here, we die also. Now therefore come, and let us go over to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9712E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9712E\"></sup>the camp of the Arameans. If they spare us, we will live; and if they kill us, we will but die.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They arose at twilight to go to the camp of the Arameans; when they came to the outskirts of the camp of the Arameans, behold, there was no one there.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9714F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9714F\"></sup>the Lord had caused the army of the Arameans to hear a sound of chariots and a sound of horses, <i>even</i> the sound of a great army, so that they said to one another, “Behold, the king of Israel has hired against us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9714G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9714G\"></sup>the kings of the Hittites and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9714H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9714H\"></sup>the kings of the Egyptians, to come upon us.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Therefore they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9715I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9715I\"></sup>arose and fled in the twilight, and left their tents and their horses and their donkeys, <i>even</i> the camp just as it was, and fled for their life.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When these lepers came to the outskirts of the camp, they entered one tent and ate and drank, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9716J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9716J\"></sup>carried from there silver and gold and clothes, and went and hid <i>them</i>; and they returned and entered another tent and carried from there <i>also</i>, and went and hid <i>them</i>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then they said to one another, “We are not doing right. This day is a day of good news, but we are keeping silent; if we wait until morning light, punishment will overtake us. Now therefore come, let us go and tell the king’s household.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So they came and called to the gatekeepers of the city, and they told them, saying, “We came to the camp of the Arameans, and behold, there was no one there, nor the voice of man, only the horses tied and the donkeys tied, and the tents just as they were.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The gatekeepers called and told <i>it</i> within the king’s household.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the king arose in the night and said to his servants, “I will now tell you what the Arameans have done to us. They know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9720K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9720K\"></sup>we are hungry; therefore they have gone from the camp <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9720L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9720L\"></sup>to hide themselves in the field, saying, ‘When they come out of the city, we will capture them alive and get into the city.’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>One of his servants said, “Please, let some <i>men</i> take five of the horses which remain, which are left in the city. Behold, they <i>will be in any case</i> like all the multitude of Israel who are left in it; behold, they <i>will be in any case</i> like all the multitude of Israel who have already perished, so let us send and see.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They took therefore two chariots with horses, and the king sent after the army of the Arameans, saying, “Go and see.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They went after them to the Jordan, and behold, all the way was full of clothes and equipment which the Arameans had thrown away in their haste. Then the messengers returned and told the king.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So the people went out and plundered the camp of the Arameans. Then a measure of fine flour <i>was sold</i> for a shekel and two measures of barley for a shekel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9724M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9724M\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now the king appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9725N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9725N\"></sup>the royal officer on whose hand he leaned to have charge of the gate; but the people trampled on him at the gate, and he died just as the man of God had said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9725O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9725O\"></sup>who spoke when the king came down to him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>It happened just as the man of God had spoken to the king, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9726P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9726P\"></sup>Two measures of barley for a shekel and a measure of fine flour for a shekel, will be <i>sold</i> tomorrow about this time at the gate of Samaria.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the royal officer answered the man of God and said, “Now behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9727Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9727Q\"></sup>if the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> should make windows in heaven, could such a thing be?” And he said, “Behold, you will see it with your own eyes, but you will not eat of it.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And so it happened to him, for the people trampled on him at the gate and he died."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9729A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9729A\"></sup>Elisha spoke to the woman whose son he had restored to life, saying, “Arise and go with your household, and sojourn wherever you can sojourn; for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9729B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9729B\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has called for a famine, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9729C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9729C\"></sup>it will even come on the land for seven years.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the woman arose and did according to the word of the man of God, and she went with her household and sojourned in the land of the Philistines seven years.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>At the end of seven years, the woman returned from the land of the Philistines; and she went out to appeal to the king for her house and for her field.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now the king was talking with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9732D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9732D\"></sup>Gehazi, the servant of the man of God, saying, “Please relate to me all the great things that Elisha has done.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>As he was relating to the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9733E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9733E\"></sup>how he had restored to life the one who was dead, behold, the woman whose son he had restored to life appealed to the king for her house and for her field. And Gehazi said, “My lord, O king, this is the woman and this is her son, whom Elisha restored to life.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the king asked the woman, she related <i>it</i> to him. So the king appointed for her a certain officer, saying, “Restore all that was hers and all the produce of the field from the day that she left the land even until now.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Elisha came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9735F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9735F\"></sup>Damascus. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9735G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9735G\"></sup>Ben-hadad king of Aram was sick, and it was told him, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9735H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9735H\"></sup>The man of God has come here.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The king said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9736I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9736I\"></sup>Hazael, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9736J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9736J\"></sup>Take a gift in your hand and go to meet the man of God, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9736K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9736K\"></sup>inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by him, saying, ‘Will I recover from this sickness?’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Hazael went to meet him and took a gift in his hand, even every kind of good thing of Damascus, forty camels’ loads; and he came and stood before him and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9737L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9737L\"></sup>Your son Ben-hadad king of Aram has sent me to you, saying, ‘Will I recover from this sickness?’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Elisha said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9738M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9738M\"></sup>Go, say to him, ‘You will surely recover,’ but the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9738N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9738N\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has shown me that he will certainly die.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He fixed his gaze steadily <i>on him</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9739O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9739O\"></sup>until he was ashamed, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9739P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9739P\"></sup>the man of God wept.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Hazael said, “Why does my lord weep?” Then he answered, “Because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9740Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9740Q\"></sup>I know the evil that you will do to the sons of Israel: their strongholds you will set on fire, and their young men you will kill with the sword, and their little ones you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9740R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9740R\"></sup>will dash in pieces, and their women with child you will rip up.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Hazael said, “But what is your servant, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9741S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9741S\"></sup><i>who is but</i> a dog, that he should do this great thing?” And Elisha answered, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9741T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9741T\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has shown me that you will be king over Aram.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So he departed from Elisha and returned to his master, who said to him, “What did Elisha say to you?” And he answered, “He told me that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9742U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9742U\"></sup>you would surely recover.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>On the following day, he took the cover and dipped it in water and spread it on his face, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9743V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9743V\"></sup>so that he died. And Hazael became king in his place.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now in the fifth year of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9744W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9744W\"></sup>Joram the son of Ahab king of Israel, Jehoshaphat being then the king of Judah, Jehoram the son of Jehoshaphat king of Judah became king.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9745X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9745X\"></sup>thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned eight years in Jerusalem.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He walked in the way of the kings of Israel, just as the house of Ahab had done, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9746Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9746Y\"></sup>the daughter of Ahab became his wife; and he did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>However, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not willing to destroy Judah, for the sake of David His servant, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9747Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9747Z\"></sup>since He had promised him to give a lamp to him through his sons always.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>In his days <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9748AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9748AA\"></sup>Edom revolted from under the hand of Judah, and made a king over themselves.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Joram crossed over to Zair, and all his chariots with him. And he arose by night and struck the Edomites who had surrounded him and the captains of the chariots; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9749AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9749AB\"></sup>but <i>his</i> army fled to their tents.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9750AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9750AC\"></sup>So Edom revolted against Judah to this day. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9750AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9750AD\"></sup>Libnah revolted at the same time.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The rest of the acts of Joram and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So Joram slept with his fathers and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9752AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9752AE\"></sup>was buried with his fathers in the city of David; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9752AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9752AF\"></sup>Ahaziah his son became king in his place.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9753AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9753AG\"></sup>In the twelfth year of Joram the son of Ahab king of Israel, Ahaziah the son of Jehoram king of Judah began to reign.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9754AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9754AH\"></sup>Ahaziah <i>was</i> twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned one year in Jerusalem. And his mother’s name <i>was</i> Athaliah the granddaughter of Omri king of Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9755AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9755AI\"></sup>He walked in the way of the house of Ahab and did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, like the house of Ahab <i>had done</i>, because he was a son-in-law of the house of Ahab.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then he went with Joram the son of Ahab to war against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9756AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9756AJ\"></sup>Hazael king of Aram at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9756AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9756AK\"></sup>Ramoth-gilead, and the Arameans wounded Joram.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9757AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9757AL\"></sup>King Joram returned to be healed in Jezreel of the wounds which the Arameans had inflicted on him at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9757AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9757AM\"></sup>Ramah when he fought against Hazael king of Aram. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9757AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9757AN\"></sup>Ahaziah the son of Jehoram king of Judah went down to see Joram the son of Ahab in Jezreel because he was sick."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Now Elisha the prophet called one of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9758A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9758A\"></sup>the sons of the prophets and said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9758B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9758B\"></sup>Gird up your loins, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9758C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9758C\"></sup>take this flask of oil in your hand and go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9758D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9758D\"></sup>Ramoth-gilead.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When you arrive there, search out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9759E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9759E\"></sup>Jehu the son of Jehoshaphat the son of Nimshi, and go in and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9759F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9759F\"></sup>bid him arise from among his brothers, and bring him to an inner room.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then take the flask of oil and pour it on his head and say, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9760G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9760G\"></sup>I have anointed you king over Israel.”’ Then open the door and flee and do not wait.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9761H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9761H\"></sup>the young man, the servant of the prophet, went to Ramoth-gilead.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When he came, behold, the captains of the army were sitting, and he said, “I have a word for you, O captain.” And Jehu said, “For which <i>one</i> of us?” And he said, “For you, O captain.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He arose and went into the house, and he poured the oil on his head and said to him, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9763I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9763I\"></sup>I have anointed you king over the people of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <i>even</i> over Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You shall strike the house of Ahab your master, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9764J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9764J\"></sup>that I may avenge <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9764K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9764K\"></sup>the blood of My servants the prophets, and the blood of all the servants of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9764L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9764L\"></sup>at the hand of Jezebel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For the whole house of Ahab shall perish, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9765M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9765M\"></sup>I will cut off from Ahab <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9765N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9765N\"></sup>every male person <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9765O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9765O\"></sup>both bond and free in Israel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9766P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9766P\"></sup>I will make the house of Ahab like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9766Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9766Q\"></sup>like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9767R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9767R\"></sup>The dogs shall eat Jezebel in the territory of Jezreel, and none shall bury <i>her</i>.’” Then he opened the door and fled.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now Jehu came out to the servants of his master, and one said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9768S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9768S\"></sup>Is all well? Why did this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9768T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9768T\"></sup>mad fellow come to you?” And he said to them, “You know <i>very well</i> the man and his talk.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They said, “It is a lie, tell us now.” And he said, “Thus and thus he said to me, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “I have anointed you king over Israel.”’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9770U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9770U\"></sup>they hurried and each man took his garment and placed it under him on the bare steps, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9770V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9770V\"></sup>blew the trumpet, saying, “Jehu is king!”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Jehu the son of Jehoshaphat the son of Nimshi conspired against Joram. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9771W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9771W\"></sup>Now Joram with all Israel was defending Ramoth-gilead against Hazael king of Aram,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9772X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9772X\"></sup>King Joram had returned to Jezreel to be healed of the wounds which the Arameans had inflicted on him when he fought with Hazael king of Aram. So Jehu said, “If this is your mind, <i>then</i> let no one escape <i>or</i> leave the city to go tell <i>it</i> in Jezreel.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Jehu rode in a chariot and went to Jezreel, for Joram was lying there. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9773Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9773Y\"></sup>Ahaziah king of Judah had come down to see Joram.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now the watchman was standing on the tower in Jezreel and he saw the company of Jehu as he came, and said, “I see a company.” And Joram said, “Take a horseman and send him to meet them and let him say, ‘Is it peace?’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So a horseman went to meet him and said, “Thus says the king, ‘Is it peace?’” And Jehu said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9775Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9775Z\"></sup>What have you to do with peace? Turn behind me.” And the watchman reported, “The messenger came to them, but he did not return.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then he sent out a second horseman, who came to them and said, “Thus says the king, ‘Is it peace?’” And Jehu answered, “What have you to do with peace? Turn behind me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The watchman reported, “He came even to them, and he did not return; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9777AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9777AA\"></sup>the driving is like the driving of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9777AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9777AB\"></sup>Jehu the son of Nimshi, for he drives furiously.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Joram said, “Get ready.” And they made his chariot ready. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9778AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9778AC\"></sup>Joram king of Israel and Ahaziah king of Judah went out, each in his chariot, and they went out to meet Jehu and found him in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9778AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9778AD\"></sup>property of Naboth the Jezreelite.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When Joram saw Jehu, he said, “Is it peace, Jehu?” And he answered, “What peace, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9779AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9779AE\"></sup>so long as the harlotries of your mother Jezebel and her witchcrafts are so many?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So Joram reined about and fled and said to Ahaziah, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9780AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9780AF\"></sup><i>There is</i> treachery, O Ahaziah!”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9781AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9781AG\"></sup>Jehu drew his bow with his full strength and shot Joram between his arms; and the arrow went through his heart and he sank in his chariot.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then <i>Jehu</i> said to Bidkar his officer, “Take <i>him</i> up and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9782AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9782AH\"></sup>cast him into the property of the field of Naboth the Jezreelite, for I remember when you and I were riding together after Ahab his father, that the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9782AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9782AI\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> laid this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9782AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9782AJ\"></sup>oracle against him:",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>‘Surely <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9783AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9783AK\"></sup>I have seen yesterday the blood of Naboth and the blood of his sons,’ says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9783AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9783AL\"></sup>I will repay you in this property,’ says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Now then, take and cast him into the property, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9784AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9784AM\"></sup>When Ahaziah the king of Judah saw <i>this</i>, he fled by the way of the garden house. And Jehu pursued him and said, “Shoot him too, in the chariot.” <i>So they shot him</i> at the ascent of Gur, which is at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9784AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9784AN\"></sup>Ibleam. But he fled to Megiddo and died there.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9785AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9785AO\"></sup>Then his servants carried him in a chariot to Jerusalem and buried him in his grave with his fathers in the city of David.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9786AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9786AP\"></sup>the eleventh year of Joram, the son of Ahab, Ahaziah became king over Judah.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When Jehu came to Jezreel, Jezebel heard <i>of it</i>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9787AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9787AQ\"></sup>she painted her eyes and adorned her head and looked out the window.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>As Jehu entered the gate, she said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9788AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9788AR\"></sup>Is it well, Zimri, your master’s murderer?”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then he lifted up his face to the window and said, “Who is on my side? Who?” And two or three officials looked down at him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He said, “Throw her down.” So they threw her down, and some of her blood was sprinkled on the wall and on the horses, and he trampled her under foot.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When he came in, he ate and drank; and he said, “See now to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9791AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9791AS\"></sup>this cursed woman and bury her, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9791AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9791AT\"></sup>she is a king’s daughter.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>They went to bury her, but they found nothing more of her than the skull and the feet and the palms of her hands.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Therefore they returned and told him. And he said, “This is the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which He spoke by His servant Elijah the Tishbite, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9793AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9793AU\"></sup>In the property of Jezreel the dogs shall eat the flesh of Jezebel;",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9794AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9794AV\"></sup>the corpse of Jezebel will be as dung on the face of the field in the property of Jezreel, so they cannot say, “This is Jezebel.”’”"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Now Ahab had seventy sons in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9795A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9795A\"></sup>Samaria. And Jehu wrote letters and sent <i>them</i> to Samaria, to the rulers of Jezreel, the elders, and to the guardians of <i>the children of</i> Ahab, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Now, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9796B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9796B\"></sup>when this letter comes to you, since your master’s sons are with you, as well as the chariots and horses and a fortified city and the weapons,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>select the best and fittest of your master’s sons, and set <i>him</i> on his father’s throne, and fight for your master’s house.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But they feared greatly and said, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9798C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9798C\"></sup>the two kings did not stand before him; how then can we stand?”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the one who <i>was</i> over the household, and he who <i>was</i> over the city, the elders, and the guardians of <i>the children</i>, sent <i>word</i> to Jehu, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9799D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9799D\"></sup>We are your servants, all that you say to us we will do, we will not make any man king; do what is good in your sight.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then he wrote a letter to them a second time saying, “If you are on my side, and you will listen to my voice, take the heads of the men, your master’s sons, and come to me at Jezreel tomorrow about this time.” Now the king’s sons, seventy persons, <i>were</i> with the great men of the city, <i>who</i> were rearing them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the letter came to them, they took the king’s sons and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9801E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9801E\"></sup>slaughtered <i>them</i>, seventy persons, and put their heads in baskets, and sent <i>them</i> to him at Jezreel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When the messenger came and told him, saying, “They have brought the heads of the king’s sons,” he said, “Put them in two heaps at the entrance of the gate until morning.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now in the morning he went out and stood and said to all the people, “You are innocent; behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9803F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9803F\"></sup>I conspired against my master and killed him, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9803G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9803G\"></sup>who killed all these?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Know then that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9804H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9804H\"></sup>there shall fall to the earth nothing of the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke concerning the house of Ahab, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has done <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9804I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9804I\"></sup>what He spoke through His servant Elijah.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Jehu killed all who remained of the house of Ahab in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9805J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9805J\"></sup>Jezreel, and all his great men and his acquaintances and his priests, until he left him without a survivor.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he arose and departed and went to Samaria. On the way while he was at Beth-eked of the shepherds,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9807K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9807K\"></sup>Jehu met the relatives of Ahaziah king of Judah and said, “Who are you?” And they answered, “We are the relatives of Ahaziah; and we have come down to greet the sons of the king and the sons of the queen mother.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He said, “Take them alive.” So they took them alive and killed them at the pit of Beth-eked, forty-two men; and he left none of them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now when he had departed from there, he met <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9809L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9809L\"></sup>Jehonadab the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9809M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9809M\"></sup>Rechab <i>coming</i> to meet him; and he greeted him and said to him, “Is your heart right, as my heart is with your heart?” And Jehonadab answered, “It is.” <i>Jehu said</i>, “If it is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9809N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9809N\"></sup>give <i>me</i> your hand.” And he gave him his hand, and he took him up to him into the chariot.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He said, “Come with me and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9810O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9810O\"></sup>see my zeal for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” So he made him ride in his chariot.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When he came to Samaria, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9811P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9811P\"></sup>he killed all who remained to Ahab in Samaria, until he had destroyed him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9811Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9811Q\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which He spoke to Elijah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Jehu gathered all the people and said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9812R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9812R\"></sup>Ahab served Baal a little; Jehu will serve him much.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9813S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9813S\"></sup>summon all the prophets of Baal, all his worshipers and all his priests; let no one be missing, for I have a great sacrifice for Baal; whoever is missing shall not live.” But Jehu did it in cunning, so that he might destroy the worshipers of Baal.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Jehu said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9814T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9814T\"></sup>Sanctify a solemn assembly for Baal.” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9814U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9814U\"></sup>they proclaimed <i>it</i>.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Jehu sent throughout Israel and all the worshipers of Baal came, so that there was not a man left who did not come. And when they went into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9815V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9815V\"></sup>the house of Baal, the house of Baal was filled from one end to the other.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He said to the one who <i>was</i> in charge of the wardrobe, “Bring out garments for all the worshipers of Baal.” So he brought out garments for them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Jehu went into the house of Baal with Jehonadab the son of Rechab; and he said to the worshipers of Baal, “Search and see that there is here with you none of the servants of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but only the worshipers of Baal.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then they went in to offer sacrifices and burnt offerings.Now Jehu had stationed for himself eighty men outside, and he had said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9818W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9818W\"></sup>The one who permits any of the men whom I bring into your hands to escape shall give up his life in exchange.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then it came about, as soon as he had finished offering the burnt offering, that Jehu said to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9819X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9819X\"></sup>guard and to the royal officers, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9819Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9819Y\"></sup>Go in, kill them; let none come out.” And they killed them with the edge of the sword; and the guard and the royal officers threw <i>them</i> out, and went to the inner room of the house of Baal.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They brought out the <i>sacred</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9820Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9820Z\"></sup>pillars of the house of Baal and burned them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>They also broke down the <i>sacred</i> pillar of Baal and broke down the house of Baal, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9821AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9821AA\"></sup>made it a latrine to this day.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Thus Jehu eradicated Baal out of Israel.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>However, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9823AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9823AB\"></sup><i>as for</i> the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, which he made Israel sin, from these Jehu did not depart, <i>even</i> the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9823AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9823AC\"></sup>golden calves that <i>were</i> at Bethel and that <i>were</i> at Dan.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Jehu, “Because you have done well in executing what is right in My eyes, <i>and</i> have done to the house of Ahab according to all that <i>was</i> in My heart, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9824AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9824AD\"></sup>your sons of the fourth generation shall sit on the throne of Israel.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But Jehu <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9825AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9825AE\"></sup>was not careful to walk in the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, with all his heart; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9825AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9825AF\"></sup>he did not depart from the sins of Jeroboam, which he made Israel sin.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>In those days the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9826AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9826AG\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> began to cut off <i>portions</i> from Israel; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9826AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9826AH\"></sup>Hazael defeated them throughout the territory of Israel:",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>from the Jordan eastward, all the land of Gilead, the Gadites and the Reubenites and the Manassites, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9827AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9827AI\"></sup>Aroer, which is by the valley of the Arnon, even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9827AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9827AJ\"></sup>Gilead and Bashan.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jehu and all that he did and all his might, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And Jehu slept with his fathers, and they buried him in Samaria. And Jehoahaz his son became king in his place.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Now the time which Jehu reigned over Israel in Samaria <i>was</i> twenty-eight years."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9831A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9831A\"></sup>When Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead, she rose and destroyed all the royal offspring.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But Jehosheba, the daughter of King Joram, sister of Ahaziah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9832B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9832B\"></sup>took Joash the son of Ahaziah and stole him from among the king’s sons who were being put to death, and placed him and his nurse in the bedroom. So they hid him from Athaliah, and he was not put to death.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So he was hidden with her in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> six years, while Athaliah was reigning over the land.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9834C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9834C\"></sup>Now in the seventh year Jehoiada sent and brought the captains of hundreds of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9834D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9834D\"></sup>the Carites and of the guard, and brought them to him in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Then he made a covenant with them and put them under oath in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and showed them the king’s son.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He commanded them, saying, “This is the thing that you shall do: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9835E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9835E\"></sup>one third of you, who come in on the sabbath and keep watch over the king’s house",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>(one third also <i>shall be</i> at the gate Sur, and one third at the gate behind the guards), shall keep watch over the house for defense.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Two parts of you, <i>even</i> all who go out on the sabbath, shall also keep watch over the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the king.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then you shall surround the king, each with his weapons in his hand; and whoever comes within the ranks shall be put to death. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9838F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9838F\"></sup>be with the king when he goes out and when he comes in.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the captains of hundreds <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9839G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9839G\"></sup>did according to all that Jehoiada the priest commanded. And each one of them took his men who were to come in on the sabbath, with those who were to go out on the sabbath, and came to Jehoiada the priest.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9840H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9840H\"></sup>The priest gave to the captains of hundreds the spears and shields that <i>had been</i> King David’s, which <i>were</i> in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The guards stood each with his weapons in his hand, from the right side of the house to the left side of the house, by the altar and by the house, around the king.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he brought the king’s son out and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9842I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9842I\"></sup>put the crown on him and <i>gave him</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9842J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9842J\"></sup>the testimony; and they made him king and anointed him, and they clapped their hands and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9842K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9842K\"></sup><i>Long</i> live the king!”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9843L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9843L\"></sup>When Athaliah heard the noise of the guard <i>and of</i> the people, she came to the people in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>She looked and behold, the king was standing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9844M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9844M\"></sup>by the pillar, according to the custom, with the captains and the trumpeters beside the king; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9844N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9844N\"></sup>all the people of the land rejoiced and blew trumpets. Then Athaliah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9844O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9844O\"></sup>tore her clothes and cried, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9844P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9844P\"></sup>Treason! Treason!”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Jehoiada the priest commanded the captains of hundreds who were appointed over the army and said to them, “Bring her out between the ranks, and whoever follows her put to death with the sword.” For the priest said, “Let her not be put to death in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So they seized her, and when she arrived at the horses’ entrance of the king’s house, she was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9846Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9846Q\"></sup>put to death there.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9847R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9847R\"></sup>Jehoiada made a covenant between the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the king and the people, that they would be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> people, also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9847S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9847S\"></sup>between the king and the people.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>All the people of the land went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9848T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9848T\"></sup>the house of Baal, and tore it down; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9848U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9848U\"></sup>his altars and his images they broke in pieces thoroughly, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9848V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9848V\"></sup>killed Mattan the priest of Baal before the altars. And the priest appointed officers over the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He took the captains of hundreds and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9849W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9849W\"></sup>Carites and the guards and all the people of the land; and they brought the king down from the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and came by the way of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9849X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9849X\"></sup>the gate of the guards to the king’s house. And he sat on the throne of the kings.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9850Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9850Y\"></sup>all the people of the land rejoiced and the city was quiet. For they had put Athaliah to death with the sword at the king’s house.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9851Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9851Z\"></sup>Jehoash was seven years old when he became king."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>In the seventh year of Jehu, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9852A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9852A\"></sup>Jehoash became king, and he reigned forty years in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name was Zibiah of Beersheba.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jehoash did right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all his days in which Jehoiada the priest instructed him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9854B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9854B\"></sup>the high places were not taken away; the people still sacrificed and burned incense on the high places.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Jehoash said to the priests, “All the money of the sacred things <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9855C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9855C\"></sup>which is brought into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in current money, <i>both</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9855D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9855D\"></sup>the money of each man’s assessment <i>and</i> all the money which any man’s heart prompts him to bring into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>let the priests take it for themselves, each from his acquaintance; and they shall repair the damages of the house wherever any damage may be found.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But it came about that in the twenty-third year of King Jehoash <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9857E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9857E\"></sup>the priests had not repaired the damages of the house.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then King Jehoash called for Jehoiada the priest, and for the <i>other</i> priests and said to them, “Why do you not repair the damages of the house? Now therefore take no <i>more</i> money from your acquaintances, but pay it for the damages of the house.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the priests agreed that they would take no <i>more</i> money from the people, nor repair the damages of the house.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9860F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9860F\"></sup>Jehoiada the priest took a chest and bored a hole in its lid and put it beside the altar, on the right side as one comes into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and the priests who guarded the threshold put in it all the money which was brought into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When they saw that there was much money in the chest, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9861G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9861G\"></sup>the king’s scribe and the high priest came up and tied <i>it</i> in bags and counted the money which was found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They gave the money which was weighed out into the hands of those who did the work, who had the oversight of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and they paid it out to the carpenters and the builders who worked on the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9863H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9863H\"></sup>to the masons and the stonecutters, and for buying timber and hewn stone to repair the damages to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and for all that was laid out for the house to repair it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9864I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9864I\"></sup>there were not made for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9864J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9864J\"></sup>silver cups, snuffers, bowls, trumpets, any vessels of gold, or vessels of silver from the money which was brought into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>for they gave that to those who did the work, and with it they repaired the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9866K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9866K\"></sup>they did not require an accounting from the men into whose hand they gave the money to pay to those who did the work, for they dealt faithfully.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9867L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9867L\"></sup>money from the guilt offerings and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9867M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9867M\"></sup>the money from the sin offerings was not brought into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9867N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9867N\"></sup>it was for the priests.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9868O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9868O\"></sup>Hazael king of Aram went up and fought against Gath and captured it, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9868P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9868P\"></sup>Hazael set his face to go up to Jerusalem.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9869Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9869Q\"></sup>Jehoash king of Judah took all the sacred things that Jehoshaphat and Jehoram and Ahaziah, his fathers, kings of Judah, had dedicated, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9869R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9869R\"></sup>his own sacred things and all the gold that was found among the treasuries of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and of the king’s house, and sent <i>them</i> to Hazael king of Aram. Then he went away from Jerusalem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Joash and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9871S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9871S\"></sup>His servants arose and made a conspiracy and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9871T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9871T\"></sup>struck down Joash at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9871U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9871U\"></sup>the house of Millo <i>as he was</i> going down to Silla.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For Jozacar the son of Shimeath and Jehozabad the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9872V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9872V\"></sup>Shomer, his servants, struck <i>him</i> and he died; and they buried him with his fathers in the city of David, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9872W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9872W\"></sup>Amaziah his son became king in his place."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>In the twenty-third year of Joash the son of Ahaziah, king of Judah, Jehoahaz the son of Jehu became king over Israel at Samaria, <i>and he reigned</i> seventeen years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and followed the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9874A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9874A\"></sup>with which he made Israel sin; he did not turn from them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9875B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9875B\"></sup>So the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was kindled against Israel, and He gave them continually into the hand of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9875C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9875C\"></sup>Hazael king of Aram, and into the hand of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9875D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9875D\"></sup>Ben-hadad the son of Hazael.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9876E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9876E\"></sup>Jehoahaz entreated the favor of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> listened to him; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9876F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9876F\"></sup>He saw the oppression of Israel, how the king of Aram oppressed them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave Israel a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9877G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9877G\"></sup>deliverer, so that they escaped from under the hand of the Arameans; and the sons of Israel lived in their tents as formerly.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Nevertheless they did not turn away from the sins of the house of Jeroboam, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9878H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9878H\"></sup>with which he made Israel sin, but walked in them; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9878I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9878I\"></sup>the Asherah also remained standing in Samaria.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For he left to Jehoahaz of the army not more than fifty horsemen and ten chariots and 10,000 footmen, for the king of Aram had destroyed them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9879J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9879J\"></sup>made them like the dust at threshing.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jehoahaz, and all that he did and his might, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Jehoahaz slept with his fathers, and they buried him in Samaria; and Joash his son became king in his place.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In the thirty-seventh year of Joash king of Judah, Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz became king over Israel in Samaria, <i>and reigned</i> sixteen years.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; he did not turn away from all the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, with which he made Israel sin, but he walked in them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9884K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9884K\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Joash and all that he did and his might with which he fought against Amaziah king of Judah, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Joash slept with his fathers, and Jeroboam sat on his throne; and Joash was buried in Samaria with the kings of Israel.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Elisha became sick with the illness of which he was to die, Joash the king of Israel came down to him and wept over him and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9886L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9886L\"></sup>My father, my father, the chariots of Israel and its horsemen!”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Elisha said to him, “Take a bow and arrows.” So he took a bow and arrows.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then he said to the king of Israel, “Put your hand on the bow.” And he put his hand <i>on it</i>, then Elisha laid his hands on the king’s hands.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He said, “Open the window toward the east,” and he opened <i>it</i>. Then Elisha said, “Shoot!” And he shot. And he said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> arrow of victory, even the arrow of victory over Aram; for you will defeat the Arameans at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9889M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9889M\"></sup>Aphek until you have destroyed <i>them</i>.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then he said, “Take the arrows,” and he took them. And he said to the king of Israel, “Strike the ground,” and he struck <i>it</i> three times and stopped.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9891N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9891N\"></sup>the man of God was angry with him and said, “You should have struck five or six times, then you would have struck Aram until you would have destroyed <i>it</i>. But now you shall strike Aram <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9891O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9891O\"></sup><i>only</i> three times.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Elisha died, and they buried him. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9892P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9892P\"></sup>the bands of the Moabites would invade the land in the spring of the year.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>As they were burying a man, behold, they saw a marauding band; and they cast the man into the grave of Elisha. And when the man touched the bones of Elisha he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9893Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9893Q\"></sup>revived and stood up on his feet.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9894R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9894R\"></sup>Hazael king of Aram had oppressed Israel all the days of Jehoahaz.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9895S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9895S\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was gracious to them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9895T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9895T\"></sup>had compassion on them and turned to them because of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9895U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9895U\"></sup>His covenant with Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, and would not destroy them or cast them from His presence until now.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When Hazael king of Aram died, Ben-hadad his son became king in his place.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9897V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9897V\"></sup>Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz took again from the hand of Ben-hadad the son of Hazael the cities which he had taken in war from the hand of Jehoahaz his father. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9897W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9897W\"></sup>Three times Joash defeated him and recovered the cities of Israel."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9898A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9898A\"></sup>In the second year of Joash son of Joahaz king of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9898B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9898B\"></sup>Amaziah the son of Joash king of Judah became king.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. And his mother’s name was Jehoaddin of Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He did right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, yet not like David his father; he did according to all that Joash his father had done.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9901C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9901C\"></sup>the high places were not taken away; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9901D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9901D\"></sup>the people still sacrificed and burned incense on the high places.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now it came about, as soon as the kingdom was firmly in his hand, that he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9902E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9902E\"></sup>killed his servants who had slain the king his father.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But the sons of the slayers he did not put to death, according to what is written in the book of the Law of Moses, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9903F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9903F\"></sup>The fathers shall not be put to death for the sons, nor the sons be put to death for the fathers; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9903G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9903G\"></sup>each shall be put to death for his own sin.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He killed <i>of</i> Edom in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9904H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9904H\"></sup>the Valley of Salt 10,000 and took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9904I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9904I\"></sup>Sela by war, and named it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9904J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9904J\"></sup>Joktheel to this day.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9905K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9905K\"></sup>Then Amaziah sent messengers to Jehoash, the son of Jehoahaz son of Jehu, king of Israel, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9905L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9905L\"></sup>Come, let us face each other.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jehoash king of Israel sent to Amaziah king of Judah, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9906M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9906M\"></sup>The thorn bush which was in Lebanon sent to the cedar which was in Lebanon, saying, ‘Give your daughter to my son in marriage.’ But there passed by a wild beast that was in Lebanon, and trampled the thorn bush.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9907N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9907N\"></sup>You have indeed defeated Edom, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9907O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9907O\"></sup>your heart has become proud. Enjoy your glory and stay at home; for why should you provoke trouble so that you, even you, would fall, and Judah with you?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Amaziah would not listen. So Jehoash king of Israel went up; and he and Amaziah king of Judah faced each other at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9908P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9908P\"></sup>Beth-shemesh, which belongs to Judah.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Judah was defeated by Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9909Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9909Q\"></sup>they fled each to his tent.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Jehoash king of Israel captured Amaziah king of Judah, the son of Jehoash the son of Ahaziah, at Beth-shemesh, and came to Jerusalem and tore down the wall of Jerusalem from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9910R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9910R\"></sup>the Gate of Ephraim to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9910S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9910S\"></sup>the Corner Gate, 400 cubits.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9911T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9911T\"></sup>He took all the gold and silver and all the utensils which were found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and in the treasuries of the king’s house, the hostages also, and returned to Samaria.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9912U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9912U\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jehoash which he did, and his might and how he fought with Amaziah king of Judah, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Jehoash slept with his fathers and was buried in Samaria with the kings of Israel; and Jeroboam his son became king in his place.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9914V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9914V\"></sup>Amaziah the son of Joash king of Judah lived fifteen years after the death of Jehoash son of Jehoahaz king of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Amaziah, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They conspired against him in Jerusalem, and he fled to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9916W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9916W\"></sup>Lachish; but they sent after him to Lachish and killed him there.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then they brought him on horses and he was buried at Jerusalem with his fathers in the city of David.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>All the people of Judah took Azariah, who <i>was</i> sixteen years old, and made him king in the place of his father Amaziah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9919X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9919X\"></sup>He built Elath and restored it to Judah after the king slept with his fathers.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In the fifteenth year of Amaziah the son of Joash king of Judah, Jeroboam the son of Joash king of Israel became king in Samaria, <i>and reigned</i> forty-one years.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; he did not depart from all the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, which he made Israel sin.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9922Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9922Y\"></sup>He restored the border of Israel from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9922Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9922Z\"></sup>the entrance of Hamath as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9922AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9922AA\"></sup>the Sea of the Arabah, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, which He spoke through His servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9922AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9922AB\"></sup>Jonah the son of Amittai, the prophet, who was of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9922AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9922AC\"></sup>Gath-hepher.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9923AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9923AD\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw the affliction of Israel, <i>which was</i> very bitter; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9923AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9923AE\"></sup>there was neither bond nor free, nor was there any helper for Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9924AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9924AF\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not say that He would blot out the name of Israel from under heaven, but He saved them by the hand of Jeroboam the son of Joash.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jeroboam and all that he did and his might, how he fought and how he recovered for Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9925AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9925AG\"></sup>Damascus and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9925AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9925AH\"></sup>Hamath, <i>which had belonged</i> to Judah, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Jeroboam slept with his fathers, even with the kings of Israel, and Zechariah his son became king in his place."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9927A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9927A\"></sup>In the twenty-seventh year of Jeroboam king of Israel, Azariah son of Amaziah king of Judah became king.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9928B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9928B\"></sup>sixteen years old when he became king, and he reigned fifty-two years in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name was Jecoliah of Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He did right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, according to all that his father Amaziah had done.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9930C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9930C\"></sup>the high places were not taken away; the people still sacrificed and burned incense on the high places.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9931D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9931D\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> struck the king, so that he was a leper to the day of his death. And he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9931E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9931E\"></sup>lived in a separate house, while Jotham the king’s son was over the household, judging the people of the land.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Azariah and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Azariah slept with his fathers, and they buried him with his fathers in the city of David, and Jotham his son became king in his place.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9934F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9934F\"></sup>In the thirty-eighth year of Azariah king of Judah, Zechariah the son of Jeroboam became king over Israel in Samaria <i>for</i> six months.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as his fathers had done; he did not depart from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, which he made Israel sin.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Shallum the son of Jabesh conspired against him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9936G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9936G\"></sup>struck him before the people and killed him, and reigned in his place.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Zechariah, behold they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>This is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9938H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9938H\"></sup>the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which He spoke to Jehu, saying, “Your sons to the fourth generation shall sit on the throne of Israel.” And so it was.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Shallum son of Jabesh became king in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9939I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9939I\"></sup>thirty-ninth year of Uzziah king of Judah, and he reigned one month in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9939J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9939J\"></sup>Samaria.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Menahem son of Gadi went up from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9940K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9940K\"></sup>Tirzah and came to Samaria, and struck Shallum son of Jabesh in Samaria, and killed him and became king in his place.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Shallum and his conspiracy which he made, behold they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Menahem struck Tiphsah and all who were in it and its borders from Tirzah, because they did not open <i>to him</i>; therefore he struck <i>it</i> and ripped up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9942L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9942L\"></sup>all its women who were with child.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>In the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9943M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9943M\"></sup>thirty-ninth year of Azariah king of Judah, Menahem son of Gadi became king over Israel <i>and reigned</i> ten years in Samaria.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; he did not depart all his days from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, which he made Israel sin.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9945N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9945N\"></sup>Pul, king of Assyria, came against the land, and Menahem gave Pul a thousand talents of silver so that his hand might be with him to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9945O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9945O\"></sup>strengthen the kingdom under his rule.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Menahem exacted the money from Israel, even from all the mighty men of wealth, from each man fifty shekels of silver to pay the king of Assyria. So the king of Assyria returned and did not remain there in the land.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Menahem and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Menahem slept with his fathers, and Pekahiah his son became king in his place.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9949P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9949P\"></sup>the fiftieth year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekahiah son of Menahem became king over Israel in Samaria, <i>and reigned</i> two years.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; he did not depart from the sins of Jeroboam son of Nebat, which he made Israel sin.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Pekah son of Remaliah, his officer, conspired against him and struck him in Samaria, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9951Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9951Q\"></sup>the castle of the king’s house with Argob and Arieh; and with him were fifty men of the Gileadites, and he killed him and became king in his place.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Pekahiah and all that he did, behold they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>In <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9953R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9953R\"></sup>the fifty-second year of Azariah king of Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9953S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9953S\"></sup>Pekah son of Remaliah became king over Israel in Samaria, <i>and reigned</i> twenty years.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; he did not depart from the sins of Jeroboam son of Nebat, which he made Israel sin.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>In the days of Pekah king of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9955T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9955T\"></sup>Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria came and captured Ijon and Abel-beth-maacah and Janoah and Kedesh and Hazor and Gilead and Galilee, all the land of Naphtali; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9955U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9955U\"></sup>he carried them captive to Assyria.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And Hoshea the son of Elah made a conspiracy against Pekah the son of Remaliah, and struck him and put him to death and became king in his place, in the twentieth year of Jotham the son of Uzziah.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Pekah and all that he did, behold, they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>In the second year of Pekah the son of Remaliah king of Israel, Jotham the son of Uzziah king of Judah became king.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9959V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9959V\"></sup>He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name <i>was</i> Jerusha the daughter of Zadok.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9960W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9960W\"></sup>He did what was right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; he did according to all that his father Uzziah had done.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9961X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9961X\"></sup>the high places were not taken away; the people still sacrificed and burned incense on the high places. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9961Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9961Y\"></sup>He built the upper gate of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jotham and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>In those days <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9963Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9963Z\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> began to send Rezin king of Aram and Pekah the son of Remaliah against Judah.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And Jotham slept with his fathers, and he was buried with his fathers in the city of David his father; and Ahaz his son became king in his place."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>In the seventeenth year of Pekah the son of Remaliah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9965A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9965A\"></sup>Ahaz the son of Jotham, king of Judah, became king.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9966B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9966B\"></sup>Ahaz <i>was</i> twenty years old when he became king, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem; and he did not do what was right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, as his father David <i>had done</i>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But he walked in the way of the kings of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9967C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9967C\"></sup>and even made his son pass through the fire, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9967D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9967D\"></sup>according to the abominations of the nations whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had driven out from before the sons of Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9968E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9968E\"></sup>sacrificed and burned incense on the high places and on the hills and under every green tree.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9969F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9969F\"></sup>Rezin king of Aram and Pekah son of Remaliah, king of Israel, came up to Jerusalem to <i>wage</i> war; and they besieged Ahaz, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9969G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9969G\"></sup>but could not overcome him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>At that time Rezin king of Aram recovered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9970H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9970H\"></sup>Elath for Aram, and cleared the Judeans out of Elath entirely; and the Arameans came to Elath and have lived there to this day.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9971I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9971I\"></sup>So Ahaz sent messengers to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9971J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9971J\"></sup>Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria, saying, “I am your servant and your son; come up and deliver me from the hand of the king of Aram and from the hand of the king of Israel, who are rising up against me.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9972K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9972K\"></sup>Ahaz took the silver and gold that was found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and in the treasuries of the king’s house, and sent a present to the king of Assyria.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9973L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9973L\"></sup>So the king of Assyria listened to him; and the king of Assyria went up against Damascus and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9973M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9973M\"></sup>captured it, and carried <i>the people of</i> it away into exile to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9973N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9973N\"></sup>Kir, and put Rezin to death.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now King Ahaz went to Damascus to meet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9974O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9974O\"></sup>Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria, and saw the altar which <i>was</i> at Damascus; and King Ahaz sent to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9974P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9974P\"></sup>Urijah the priest the pattern of the altar and its model, according to all its workmanship.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Urijah the priest built an altar; according to all that King Ahaz had sent from Damascus, thus Urijah the priest made <i>it</i>, before the coming of King Ahaz from Damascus.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When the king came from Damascus, the king saw the altar; then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9976Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9976Q\"></sup>the king approached the altar and went up to it,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and burned his burnt offering and his meal offering, and poured his drink offering and sprinkled the blood of his peace offerings on the altar.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9978R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9978R\"></sup>The bronze altar, which <i>was</i> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he brought from the front of the house, from between <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9978S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9978S\"></sup><i>his</i> altar and the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he put it on the north side of <i>his</i> altar.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then King Ahaz commanded Urijah the priest, saying, “Upon the great altar burn <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9979T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9979T\"></sup>the morning burnt offering and the evening meal offering and the king’s burnt offering and his meal offering, with the burnt offering of all the people of the land and their meal offering and their drink offerings; and sprinkle on it all the blood of the burnt offering and all the blood of the sacrifice. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9979U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9979U\"></sup>the bronze altar shall be for me to inquire <i>by</i>.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Urijah the priest did according to all that King Ahaz commanded.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then King Ahaz <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9981V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9981V\"></sup>cut off the borders of the stands, and removed the laver from them; he also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9981W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9981W\"></sup>took down the sea from the bronze oxen which were under it and put it on a pavement of stone.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The covered way for the sabbath which they had built in the house, and the outer entry of the king, he removed from the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> because of the king of Assyria.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Ahaz which he did, are they not written <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9983X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9983X\"></sup>in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9984Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9984Y\"></sup>Ahaz slept with his fathers, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9984Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9984Z\"></sup>was buried with his fathers in the city of David; and his son Hezekiah reigned in his place."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>In the twelfth year of Ahaz king of Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9985A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9985A\"></sup>Hoshea the son of Elah became king over Israel in Samaria, <i>and reigned</i> nine years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, only not as the kings of Israel who were before him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9987B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9987B\"></sup>Shalmaneser king of Assyria came up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9987C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9987C\"></sup>against him, and Hoshea became his servant and paid him tribute.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the king of Assyria found conspiracy in Hoshea, who had sent messengers to So king of Egypt and had offered no tribute to the king of Assyria, as <i>he had done</i> year by year; so the king of Assyria shut him up and bound him in prison.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the king of Assyria invaded the whole land and went up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9989D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9989D\"></sup>Samaria and besieged it three years.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In the ninth year of Hoshea, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9990E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9990E\"></sup>the king of Assyria captured Samaria and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9990F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9990F\"></sup>carried Israel away into exile to Assyria, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9990G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9990G\"></sup>settled them in Halah and Habor, <i>on</i> the river of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9990H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9990H\"></sup>Gozan, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9990I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9990I\"></sup>in the cities of the Medes.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9991J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9991J\"></sup><i>this</i> came about because the sons of Israel had sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9991K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9991K\"></sup>who had brought them up from the land of Egypt from under the hand of Pharaoh, king of Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9991L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9991L\"></sup>and they had feared other gods",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9992M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9992M\"></sup>walked in the customs of the nations whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had driven out before the sons of Israel, and <i>in the customs</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9992N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9992N\"></sup>of the kings of Israel which they had introduced.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sons of Israel did things secretly which were not right against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God. Moreover, they built for themselves high places in all their towns, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9993O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9993O\"></sup>watchtower to fortified city.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9994P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9994P\"></sup>They set for themselves <i>sacred</i> pillars and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9994Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9994Q\"></sup>Asherim on every high hill and under every green tree,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and there they burned incense on all the high places as the nations <i>did</i> which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had carried away to exile before them; and they did evil things provoking the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They served idols, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9996R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9996R\"></sup>concerning which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said to them, “You shall not do this thing.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Yet the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9997S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9997S\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> warned Israel and Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9997T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9997T\"></sup>through all His prophets <i>and</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9997U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9997U\"></sup>every seer, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9997V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9997V\"></sup>Turn from your evil ways and keep My commandments, My statutes according to all the law which I commanded your fathers, and which I sent to you through My servants the prophets.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>However, they did not listen, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9998W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9998W\"></sup>stiffened their neck like their fathers, who did not believe in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9999X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9999X\"></sup>They rejected His statutes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9999Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9999Y\"></sup>His covenant which He made with their fathers and His warnings with which He warned them. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9999Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9999Z\"></sup>they followed vanity and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9999AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9999AA\"></sup>became vain, and <i>went</i> after the nations which surrounded them, concerning which the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9999AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9999AB\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded them not to do like them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They forsook all the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God and made for themselves molten images, <i>even</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10000AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10000AC\"></sup>two calves, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10000AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10000AD\"></sup>made an Asherah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10000AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10000AE\"></sup>worshiped all the host of heaven and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10000AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10000AF\"></sup>served Baal.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10001AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10001AG\"></sup>they made their sons and their daughters pass through the fire, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10001AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10001AH\"></sup>practiced divination and enchantments, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10001AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10001AI\"></sup>sold themselves to do evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, provoking Him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was very angry with Israel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10002AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10002AJ\"></sup>removed them from His sight; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10002AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10002AK\"></sup>none was left except the tribe of Judah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10003AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10003AL\"></sup>Judah did not keep the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10003AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10003AM\"></sup>walked in the customs which Israel had introduced.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rejected all the descendants of Israel and afflicted them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10004AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10004AN\"></sup>gave them into the hand of plunderers, until He had cast them out of His sight.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10005AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10005AO\"></sup>He had torn Israel from the house of David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10005AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10005AP\"></sup>they made Jeroboam the son of Nebat king. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10005AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10005AQ\"></sup>Jeroboam drove Israel away from following the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and made them commit a great sin.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The sons of Israel walked in all the sins of Jeroboam which he did; they did not depart from them",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10007AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10007AR\"></sup>until the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> removed Israel from His sight, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10007AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10007AS\"></sup>as He spoke through all His servants the prophets. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10007AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10007AT\"></sup>So Israel was carried away into exile from their own land to Assyria until this day.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10008AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10008AU\"></sup>The king of Assyria brought <i>men</i> from Babylon and from Cuthah and from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10008AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10008AV\"></sup>Avva and from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10008AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10008AW\"></sup>Hamath and Sepharvaim, and settled <i>them</i> in the cities of Samaria in place of the sons of Israel. So they possessed Samaria and lived in its cities.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>At the beginning of their living there, they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10009AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10009AX\"></sup>did not fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent lions among them which killed some of them.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So they spoke to the king of Assyria, saying, “The nations whom you have carried away into exile in the cities of Samaria do not know the custom of the god of the land; so he has sent lions among them, and behold, they kill them because they do not know the custom of the god of the land.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then the king of Assyria commanded, saying, “Take there one of the priests whom you carried away into exile and let him go and live there; and let him teach them the custom of the god of the land.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So one of the priests whom they had carried away into exile from Samaria came and lived at Bethel, and taught them how they should fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But every nation still made gods of its own and put them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10013AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10013AY\"></sup>in the houses of the high places which the people of Samaria had made, every nation in their cities in which they lived.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10014AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10014AZ\"></sup>The men of Babylon made Succoth-benoth, the men of Cuth made Nergal, the men of Hamath made Ashima,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and the Avvites made Nibhaz and Tartak; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10015BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10015BA\"></sup>the Sepharvites burned their children in the fire to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10015BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10015BB\"></sup>Adrammelech and Anammelech the gods of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10015BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10015BC\"></sup>Sepharvaim.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10016BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10016BD\"></sup>They also feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10016BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10016BE\"></sup>appointed from among themselves priests of the high places, who acted for them in the houses of the high places.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>They feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and served their own gods according to the custom of the nations from among whom they had been carried away into exile.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>To this day they do according to the earlier customs: they do not fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, nor do they follow their statutes or their ordinances or the law, or the commandments which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded the sons of Jacob, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10018BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10018BF\"></sup>whom He named Israel;",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>with whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made a covenant and commanded them, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10019BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10019BG\"></sup>You shall not fear other gods, nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10019BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10019BH\"></sup>bow down yourselves to them nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10019BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10019BI\"></sup>serve them nor sacrifice to them.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10020BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10020BJ\"></sup>who brought you up from the land of Egypt with great power and with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10020BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10020BK\"></sup>an outstretched arm, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10020BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10020BL\"></sup>Him you shall fear, and to Him you shall bow yourselves down, and to Him you shall sacrifice.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The statutes and the ordinances and the law and the commandment which He wrote for you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10021BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10021BM\"></sup>you shall observe to do forever; and you shall not fear other gods.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The covenant that I have made with you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10022BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10022BN\"></sup>you shall not forget, nor shall you fear other gods.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God you shall fear; and He will deliver you from the hand of all your enemies.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>However, they did not listen, but they did according to their earlier custom.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10025BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10025BO\"></sup>So while these nations feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, they also served their idols; their children likewise and their grandchildren, as their fathers did, so they do to this day."
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Now it came about <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10026A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10026A\"></sup>in the third year of Hoshea, the son of Elah king of Israel, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10026B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10026B\"></sup>Hezekiah the son of Ahaz king of Judah became king.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10027C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10027C\"></sup>twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name was Abi the daughter of Zechariah.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10028D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10028D\"></sup>He did right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, according to all that his father David had done.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10029E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10029E\"></sup>He removed the high places and broke down the <i>sacred</i> pillars and cut down the Asherah. He also broke in pieces <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10029F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10029F\"></sup>the bronze serpent that Moses had made, for until those days the sons of Israel burned incense to it; and it was called Nehushtan.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10030G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10030G\"></sup>He trusted in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10030H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10030H\"></sup>so that after him there was none like him among all the kings of Judah, nor <i>among those</i> who were before him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10031I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10031I\"></sup>clung to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; he did not depart from following Him, but kept His commandments, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10032J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10032J\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with him; wherever he went he prospered. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10032K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10032K\"></sup>he rebelled against the king of Assyria and did not serve him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10033L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10033L\"></sup>He defeated the Philistines as far as Gaza and its territory, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10033M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10033M\"></sup>watchtower to fortified city.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now in the fourth year of King Hezekiah, which was the seventh year of Hoshea son of Elah king of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10034N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10034N\"></sup>Shalmaneser king of Assyria came up against Samaria and besieged it.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>At the end of three years they captured it; in the sixth year of Hezekiah, which was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10035O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10035O\"></sup>the ninth year of Hoshea king of Israel, Samaria was captured.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the king of Assyria carried Israel away into exile to Assyria, and put them in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10036P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10036P\"></sup>Halah and on the Habor, the river of Gozan, and in the cities of the Medes,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>because they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10037Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10037Q\"></sup>did not obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, but transgressed His covenant, <i>even</i> all that Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded; they would neither listen nor do <i>it</i>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10038R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10038R\"></sup>Now in the fourteenth year of King Hezekiah, Sennacherib king of Assyria came up against all the fortified cities of Judah and seized them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Hezekiah king of Judah sent to the king of Assyria at Lachish, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10039S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10039S\"></sup>I have done wrong. Withdraw from me; whatever you impose on me I will bear.” So the king of Assyria required of Hezekiah king of Judah three hundred talents of silver and thirty talents of gold.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10040T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10040T\"></sup>Hezekiah gave <i>him</i> all the silver which was found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and in the treasuries of the king’s house.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>At that time Hezekiah cut off <i>the gold from</i> the doors of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <i>from</i> the doorposts which Hezekiah king of Judah had overlaid, and gave it to the king of Assyria.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the king of Assyria sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10042U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10042U\"></sup>Tartan and Rab-saris and Rabshakeh from Lachish to King Hezekiah with a large army to Jerusalem. So they went up and came to Jerusalem. And when they went up, they came and stood by the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10042V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10042V\"></sup>conduit of the upper pool, which is on the highway of the fuller’s field.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When they called to the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10043W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10043W\"></sup>Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was over the household, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10043X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10043X\"></sup>Shebnah the scribe and Joah the son of Asaph the recorder, came out to them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Rabshakeh said to them, “Say now to Hezekiah, ‘Thus says the great king, the king of Assyria, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10044Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10044Y\"></sup>What is this confidence that you have?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You say (but <i>they are</i> only empty words), ‘<i>I have</i> counsel and strength for the war.’ Now on whom do you rely, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10045Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10045Z\"></sup>that you have rebelled against me?",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Now behold, you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10046AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10046AA\"></sup>rely on the staff of this crushed reed, <i>even</i> on Egypt; on which if a man leans, it will go into his hand and pierce it. So is Pharaoh king of Egypt to all who rely on him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But if you say to me, ‘We trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God,’ is it not He whose high places and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10047AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10047AB\"></sup>whose altars Hezekiah has taken away, and has said to Judah and to Jerusalem, ‘You shall worship before this altar in Jerusalem’?",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now therefore, come, make a bargain with my master the king of Assyria, and I will give you two thousand horses, if you are able on your part to set riders on them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>How then can you repulse one official of the least of my master’s servants, and rely on Egypt for chariots and for horsemen?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Have I now come up without the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> approval against this place to destroy it? The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘Go up against this land and destroy it.’”’”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, and Shebnah and Joah, said to Rabshakeh, “Speak now to your servants in Aramaic, for we understand <i>it</i>; and do not speak with us in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10051AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10051AC\"></sup>Judean in the hearing of the people who are on the wall.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But Rabshakeh said to them, “Has my master sent me only to your master and to you to speak these words, <i>and</i> not to the men who sit on the wall, <i>doomed</i> to eat their own dung and drink their own urine with you?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Rabshakeh stood and cried with a loud voice in Judean, saying, “Hear the word of the great king, the king of Assyria.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Thus says the king, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10054AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10054AD\"></sup>Do not let Hezekiah deceive you, for he will not be able to deliver you from my hand;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>nor let Hezekiah make you trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will surely deliver us, and this city will not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Do not listen to Hezekiah, for thus says the king of Assyria, “Make your peace with me and come out to me, and eat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10056AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10056AE\"></sup>each of his vine and each of his fig tree and drink each of the waters of his own cistern,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>until I come and take you away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10057AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10057AF\"></sup>to a land like your own land, a land of grain and new wine, a land of bread and vineyards, a land of olive trees and honey, that you may live and not die.” But do not listen to Hezekiah when he misleads you, saying, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will deliver us.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10058AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10058AG\"></sup>Has any one of the gods of the nations delivered his land from the hand of the king of Assyria?",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10059AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10059AH\"></sup>Where are the gods of Hamath and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10059AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10059AI\"></sup>Arpad? Where are the gods of Sepharvaim, Hena and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10059AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10059AJ\"></sup>Ivvah? Have they delivered Samaria from my hand?",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Who among all the gods of the lands have delivered their land from my hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10060AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10060AK\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> should deliver Jerusalem from my hand?’”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>But the people were silent and answered him not a word, for the king’s commandment was, “Do not answer him.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10062AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10062AL\"></sup>Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was over the household, and Shebna the scribe and Joah the son of Asaph, the recorder, came to Hezekiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10062AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10062AM\"></sup>with their clothes torn and told him the words of Rabshakeh."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10063A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10063A\"></sup>And when King Hezekiah heard <i>it</i>, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10063B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10063B\"></sup>tore his clothes, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10063C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10063C\"></sup>covered himself with sackcloth and entered the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then he sent Eliakim who was over the household with Shebna the scribe and the elders of the priests, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10064D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10064D\"></sup>covered with sackcloth, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10064E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10064E\"></sup>Isaiah the prophet the son of Amoz.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They said to him, “Thus says Hezekiah, ‘This day is a day of distress, rebuke, and rejection; for children have come to birth and there is no strength to <i>deliver</i>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10066F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10066F\"></sup>Perhaps the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will hear all the words of Rabshakeh, whom his master the king of Assyria has sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10066G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10066G\"></sup>to reproach the living God, and will rebuke the words which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has heard. Therefore, offer a prayer for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10066H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10066H\"></sup>the remnant that is left.’”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So the servants of King Hezekiah came to Isaiah.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Isaiah said to them, “Thus you shall say to your master, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Do not be afraid because of the words that you have heard, with which the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10068I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10068I\"></sup>servants of the king of Assyria <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10068J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10068J\"></sup>have blasphemed Me.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Behold, I will put a spirit in him so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10069K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10069K\"></sup>he will hear a rumor and return to his own land. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10069L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10069L\"></sup>I will make him fall by the sword in his own land.”’”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Rabshakeh returned and found the king of Assyria fighting against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10070M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10070M\"></sup>Libnah, for he had heard that the king had left <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10070N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10070N\"></sup>Lachish.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When he heard <i>them</i> say concerning Tirhakah king of Cush, “Behold, he has come out to fight against you,” he sent messengers again to Hezekiah saying,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Thus you shall say to Hezekiah king of Judah, ‘Do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10072O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10072O\"></sup>let your God in whom you trust deceive you saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10072P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10072P\"></sup>Jerusalem will not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Behold, you have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all the lands, destroying them completely. So will you be spared?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10074Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10074Q\"></sup>Did the gods of those nations which my fathers destroyed deliver them, <i>even</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10074R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10074R\"></sup>Gozan and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10074S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10074S\"></sup>Haran and Rezeph and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10074T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10074T\"></sup>the sons of Eden who <i>were</i> in Telassar?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10075U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10075U\"></sup>Where is the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad, the king of the city of Sepharvaim, and <i>of</i> Hena and Ivvah?’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10076V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10076V\"></sup>Hezekiah took the letter from the hand of the messengers and read it, and he went up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and spread it out before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Hezekiah prayed before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10077W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10077W\"></sup>who are enthroned <i>above</i> the cherubim, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10077X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10077X\"></sup>You are the God, You alone, of all the kingdoms of the earth. You have made heaven and earth.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10078Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10078Y\"></sup>Incline Your ear, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and hear; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10078Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10078Z\"></sup>open Your eyes, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and see; and listen to the words of Sennacherib, which he has sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10078AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10078AA\"></sup>to reproach the living God.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Truly, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the kings of Assyria have devastated the nations and their lands",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and have cast their gods into the fire, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10080AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10080AB\"></sup>for they were not gods but the work of men’s hands, wood and stone. So they have destroyed them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, I pray, deliver us from his hand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10081AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10081AC\"></sup>that all the kingdoms of the earth may know that You alone, O <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10081AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10081AD\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, are God.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Isaiah the son of Amoz sent to Hezekiah saying, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, ‘Because you have prayed to Me about Sennacherib king of Assyria, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10082AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10082AE\"></sup>I have heard <i>you</i>.’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>This is the word that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken against him:‘She has despised you and mocked you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10083AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10083AF\"></sup>The virgin daughter of Zion;She <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10083AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10083AG\"></sup>has shaken <i>her</i> head behind you,The daughter of Jerusalem!",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>‘Whom have you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10084AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10084AH\"></sup>reproached and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10084AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10084AI\"></sup>blasphemed?And against whom have you raised <i>your</i> voice,And haughtily lifted up your eyes?Against the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10084AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10084AJ\"></sup>Holy One of Israel!",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10085AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10085AK\"></sup>Through your messengers you have reproached the Lord,And you have said, “With my many chariotsI came up to the heights of the mountains,To the remotest parts of Lebanon;And I cut down its tall cedars <i>and</i> its choice cypresses.And I entered its farthest lodging place, its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10085AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10085AL\"></sup>thickest forest.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“I dug <i>wells</i> and drank foreign waters,And with the sole of my feet I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10086AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10086AM\"></sup>dried upAll the rivers of Egypt.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10087AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10087AN\"></sup>Have you not heard?Long ago I did it;From ancient times I planned it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10087AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10087AO\"></sup>Now I have brought it to pass,That you should turn fortified cities into ruinous heaps.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>‘Therefore their inhabitants were short of strength,They were dismayed and put to shame;They were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10088AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10088AP\"></sup>as the vegetation of the field and as the green herb,As grass on the housetops is scorched before it is grown up.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>‘But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10089AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10089AQ\"></sup>I know your sitting down,And your going out and your coming in,And your raging against Me.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>‘Because of your raging against Me,And because your arrogance has come up to My ears,Therefore I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10090AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10090AR\"></sup>will put My hook in your nose,And My bridle in your lips,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10090AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10090AS\"></sup>I will turn you back by the way which you came.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>‘Then this shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10091AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10091AT\"></sup>the sign for you: you will eat this year what grows of itself, in the second year what springs from the same, and in the third year sow, reap, plant vineyards, and eat their fruit.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10092AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10092AU\"></sup>The surviving remnant of the house of Judah will again take root downward and bear fruit upward.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For out of Jerusalem will go forth a remnant, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10093AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10093AV\"></sup>out of Mount Zion survivors. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10093AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10093AW\"></sup>The zeal of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will perform this.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>‘Therefore thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> concerning the king of Assyria, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10094AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10094AX\"></sup>He will not come to this city or shoot an arrow there; and he will not come before it with a shield or throw up a siege ramp against it.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10095AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10095AY\"></sup>By the way that he came, by the same he will return, and he shall not come to this city,”’ declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10096AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10096AZ\"></sup>For I will defend this city to save it for My own sake and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10096BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10096BA\"></sup>for My servant David’s sake.’”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10097BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10097BB\"></sup>Then it happened that night that the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> went out and struck 185,000 in the camp of the Assyrians; and when men rose early in the morning, behold, all of them were dead.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10098BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10098BC\"></sup>Sennacherib king of Assyria departed and returned <i>home</i>, and lived at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10098BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10098BD\"></sup>Nineveh.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>It came about as he was worshiping in the house of Nisroch his god, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10099BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10099BE\"></sup>Adrammelech and Sharezer killed him with the sword; and they escaped into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10099BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10099BF\"></sup>the land of Ararat. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10099BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10099BG\"></sup>Esarhaddon his son became king in his place."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10100A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10100A\"></sup>In those days Hezekiah became mortally ill. And Isaiah the prophet the son of Amoz came to him and said to him, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10100B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10100B\"></sup>Set your house in order, for you shall die and not live.’”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then he turned his face to the wall and prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10102C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10102C\"></sup>Remember now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I beseech You, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10102D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10102D\"></sup>how I have walked before You in truth and with a whole heart and have done what is good in Your sight.” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10102E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10102E\"></sup>Hezekiah wept bitterly.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Before Isaiah had gone out of the middle court, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to him, saying,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Return and say to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10104F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10104F\"></sup>Hezekiah the leader of My people, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your father David, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10104G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10104G\"></sup>I have heard your prayer, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10104H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10104H\"></sup>I have seen your tears; behold, I will heal you. On the third day you shall go up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I will add fifteen years to your life, and I will deliver you and this city from the hand of the king of Assyria; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10105I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10105I\"></sup>I will defend this city for My own sake and for My servant David’s sake.”’”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Isaiah said, “Take a cake of figs.” And they took and laid <i>it</i> on the boil, and he recovered.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now Hezekiah said to Isaiah, “What will be the sign that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will heal me, and that I shall go up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the third day?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Isaiah said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10108J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10108J\"></sup>This shall be the sign to you from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do the thing that He has spoken: shall the shadow go forward ten steps or go back ten steps?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So Hezekiah answered, “It is easy for the shadow to decline ten steps; no, but let the shadow turn backward ten steps.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Isaiah the prophet cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10110K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10110K\"></sup>He brought the shadow on the stairway back ten steps by which it had gone down on the stairway of Ahaz.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10111L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10111L\"></sup>At that time Berodach-baladan a son of Baladan, king of Babylon, sent letters and a present to Hezekiah, for he heard that Hezekiah had been sick.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Hezekiah listened to them, and showed them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10112M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10112M\"></sup>all his treasure house, the silver and the gold and the spices and the precious oil and the house of his armor and all that was found in his treasuries. There was nothing in his house nor in all his dominion that Hezekiah did not show them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Isaiah the prophet came to King Hezekiah and said to him, “What did these men say, and from where have they come to you?” And Hezekiah said, “They have come from a far country, from Babylon.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He said, “What have they seen in your house?” So Hezekiah answered, “They have seen all that is in my house; there is nothing among my treasuries that I have not shown them.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, “Hear the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>‘Behold, the days are coming when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10116N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10116N\"></sup>all that is in your house, and all that your fathers have laid up in store to this day will be carried to Babylon; nothing shall be left,’ says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>‘Some <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10117O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10117O\"></sup>of your sons who shall issue from you, whom you will beget, will be taken away; and they will become <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10117P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10117P\"></sup>officials in the palace of the king of Babylon.’”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Hezekiah said to Isaiah, “The word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which you have spoken is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10118Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10118Q\"></sup>good.” For he thought, “Is it not so, if there will be peace and truth in my days?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10119R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10119R\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Hezekiah and all his might, and how he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10119S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10119S\"></sup>made the pool and the conduit and brought water into the city, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10120T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10120T\"></sup>So Hezekiah slept with his fathers, and Manasseh his son became king in his place."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10121A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10121A\"></sup>Manasseh was twelve years old when he became king, and he reigned fifty-five years in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name was Hephzibah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10122B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10122B\"></sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10122C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10122C\"></sup>according to the abominations of the nations whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> dispossessed before the sons of Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10123D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10123D\"></sup>he rebuilt the high places which Hezekiah his father had destroyed; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10123E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10123E\"></sup>he erected altars for Baal and made an Asherah, as Ahab king of Israel had done, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10123F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10123F\"></sup>worshiped all the host of heaven and served them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10124G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10124G\"></sup>He built altars in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10124H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10124H\"></sup>In Jerusalem I will put My name.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For he built altars for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10125I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10125I\"></sup>all the host of heaven in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10125J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10125J\"></sup>the two courts of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10126K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10126K\"></sup>He made his son pass through the fire, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10126L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10126L\"></sup>practiced witchcraft and used divination, and dealt with mediums and spiritists. He did much evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> provoking <i>Him to anger</i>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10127M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10127M\"></sup>he set the carved image of Asherah that he had made, in the house of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to David and to his son Solomon, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10127N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10127N\"></sup>In this house and in Jerusalem, which I have chosen from all the tribes of Israel, I will put My name forever.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10128O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10128O\"></sup>will not make the feet of Israel wander anymore from the land which I gave their fathers, if only they will observe to do according to all that I have commanded them, and according to all the law that My servant Moses commanded them.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But they did not listen, and Manasseh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10129P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10129P\"></sup>seduced them to do evil more than the nations whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> destroyed before the sons of Israel.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke through His servants the prophets, saying,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10131Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10131Q\"></sup>Because Manasseh king of Judah has done these abominations, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10131R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10131R\"></sup>having done wickedly more than all the Amorites did who <i>were</i> before him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10131S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10131S\"></sup>has also made Judah sin <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10131T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10131T\"></sup>with his idols;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>therefore thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, ‘Behold, I am bringing <i>such</i> calamity on Jerusalem and Judah, that whoever hears of it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10132U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10132U\"></sup>both his ears will tingle.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10133V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10133V\"></sup>I will stretch over Jerusalem the line of Samaria and the plummet of the house of Ahab, and I will wipe Jerusalem as one wipes a dish, wiping it and turning it upside down.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I will abandon the remnant of My inheritance and deliver them into the hand of their enemies, and they will become as plunder and spoil to all their enemies;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>because they have done evil in My sight, and have been provoking Me to anger since the day their fathers came from Egypt, even to this day.’”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10136W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10136W\"></sup>Moreover, Manasseh shed very much innocent blood until he had filled Jerusalem from one end to another; besides his sin <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10136X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10136X\"></sup>with which he made Judah sin, in doing evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10137Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10137Y\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Manasseh and all that he did and his sin which he committed, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10138Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10138Z\"></sup>And Manasseh slept with his fathers and was buried in the garden of his own house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10138AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10138AA\"></sup>in the garden of Uzza, and Amon his son became king in his place.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10139AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10139AB\"></sup>Amon was twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned two years in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name <i>was</i> Meshullemeth the daughter of Haruz of Jotbah.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10140AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10140AC\"></sup>as Manasseh his father had done.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For he walked in all the way that his father had walked, and served the idols that his father had served and worshiped them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10142AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10142AD\"></sup>he forsook the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of his fathers, and did not walk in the way of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10143AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10143AE\"></sup>The servants of Amon conspired against him and killed the king in his own house.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10144AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10144AF\"></sup>the people of the land killed all those who had conspired against King Amon, and the people of the land made Josiah his son king in his place.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Amon which he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He was buried in his grave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10146AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10146AG\"></sup>in the garden of Uzza, and Josiah his son became king in his place."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10147A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10147A\"></sup>Josiah was eight years old when he became king, and he reigned thirty-one years in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name <i>was</i> Jedidah the daughter of Adaiah of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10147B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10147B\"></sup>Bozkath.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and walked in all the way of his father David, nor did he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10148C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10148C\"></sup>turn aside to the right or to the left.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10149D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10149D\"></sup>in the eighteenth year of King Josiah, the king sent Shaphan, the son of Azaliah the son of Meshullam the scribe, to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saying,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10150E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10150E\"></sup>Go up to Hilkiah the high priest that he may count the money brought in to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which the doorkeepers have gathered from the people.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10151F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10151F\"></sup>Let them deliver it into the hand of the workmen who have the oversight of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and let them give it to the workmen who are in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to repair the damages of the house,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>to the carpenters and the builders and the masons and for buying timber and hewn stone to repair the house.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10153G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10153G\"></sup>no accounting shall be made with them for the money delivered into their hands, for they deal faithfully.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Hilkiah the high priest said to Shaphan the scribe, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10154H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10154H\"></sup>I have found the book of the law in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And Hilkiah gave the book to Shaphan who read it.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Shaphan the scribe came to the king and brought back word to the king and said, “Your servants have emptied out the money that was found in the house, and have delivered it into the hand of the workmen who have the oversight of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Moreover, Shaphan the scribe told the king saying, “Hilkiah the priest has given me a book.” And Shaphan read it in the presence of the king.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When the king heard the words of the book of the law, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10157I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10157I\"></sup>he tore his clothes.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the king commanded Hilkiah the priest, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10158J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10158J\"></sup>Ahikam the son of Shaphan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10158K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10158K\"></sup>Achbor the son of Micaiah, Shaphan the scribe, and Asaiah the king’s servant saying,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Go, inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for me and the people and all Judah concerning the words of this book that has been found, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10159L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10159L\"></sup>great is the wrath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that burns against us, because our fathers have not listened to the words of this book, to do according to all that is written concerning us.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Hilkiah the priest, Ahikam, Achbor, Shaphan, and Asaiah went to Huldah the prophetess, the wife of Shallum the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10160M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10160M\"></sup>Tikvah, the son of Harhas, keeper of the wardrobe (now she lived in Jerusalem in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10160N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10160N\"></sup>Second Quarter); and they spoke to her.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>She said to them, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, ‘Tell the man who sent you to me,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Behold, I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10162O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10162O\"></sup>bring evil on this place and on its inhabitants, <i>even</i> all the words of the book which the king of Judah has read.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10163P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10163P\"></sup>Because they have forsaken Me and have burned incense to other gods that they might provoke Me to anger with all the work of their hands, therefore My wrath burns against this place, and it shall not be quenched.”’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10164Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10164Q\"></sup>the king of Judah who sent you to inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> thus shall you say to him, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, “<i>Regarding</i> the words which you have heard,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10165R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10165R\"></sup>because your heart was tender and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10165S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10165S\"></sup>you humbled yourself before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> when you heard what I spoke against this place and against its inhabitants that they should become <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10165T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10165T\"></sup>a desolation and a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10165U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10165U\"></sup>curse, and you have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10165V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10165V\"></sup>torn your clothes and wept before Me, I truly have heard you,” declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“Therefore, behold, I will gather you to your fathers, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10166W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10166W\"></sup>you will be gathered to your grave in peace, and your eyes will not see all the evil which I will bring on this place.”’” So they brought back word to the king."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10167A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10167A\"></sup>Then the king sent, and they gathered to him all the elders of Judah and of Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The king went up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and all the men of Judah and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem with him, and the priests and the prophets and all the people, both small and great; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10168B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10168B\"></sup>he read in their hearing all the words of the book of the covenant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10168C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10168C\"></sup>which was found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10169D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10169D\"></sup>The king stood by the pillar and made a covenant before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10169E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10169E\"></sup>to walk after the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and to keep His commandments and His testimonies and His statutes with all <i>his</i> heart and all <i>his</i> soul, to carry out the words of this covenant that were written in this book. And all the people entered into the covenant.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the king commanded Hilkiah the high priest and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10170F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10170F\"></sup>the priests of the second order and the doorkeepers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10170G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10170G\"></sup>to bring out of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all the vessels that were made for Baal, for Asherah, and for all the host of heaven; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10170H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10170H\"></sup>he burned them outside Jerusalem in the fields of the Kidron, and carried their ashes to Bethel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He did away with the idolatrous priests whom the kings of Judah had appointed to burn incense in the high places in the cities of Judah and in the surrounding area of Jerusalem, also those who burned incense to Baal, to the sun and to the moon and to the constellations and to all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10171I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10171I\"></sup>host of heaven.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He brought out the Asherah from the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> outside Jerusalem to the brook Kidron, and burned it at the brook Kidron, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10172J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10172J\"></sup>ground <i>it</i> to dust, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10172K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10172K\"></sup>threw its dust on the graves of the common people.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He also broke down the houses of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10173L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10173L\"></sup><i>male</i> cult prostitutes which <i>were</i> in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, where <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10173M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10173M\"></sup>the women were weaving hangings for the Asherah.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then he brought all the priests from the cities of Judah, and defiled the high places where the priests had burned incense, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10174N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10174N\"></sup>Geba to Beersheba; and he broke down the high places of the gates which <i>were</i> at the entrance of the gate of Joshua the governor of the city, which <i>were</i> on one’s left at the city gate.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Nevertheless <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10175O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10175O\"></sup>the priests of the high places did not go up to the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem, but they ate unleavened bread among their brothers.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10176P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10176P\"></sup>He also defiled Topheth, which is in the valley of the son of Hinnom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10176Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10176Q\"></sup>that no man might make his son or his daughter pass through the fire for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10176R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10176R\"></sup>Molech.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He did away with the horses which the kings of Judah had given to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10177S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10177S\"></sup>sun, at the entrance of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, by the chamber of Nathan-melech the official, which <i>was</i> in the precincts; and he burned the chariots of the sun with fire.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10178T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10178T\"></sup>The altars which <i>were</i> on the roof, the upper chamber of Ahaz, which the kings of Judah had made, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10178U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10178U\"></sup>the altars which Manasseh had made in the two courts of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the king broke down; and he smashed them there and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10178V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10178V\"></sup>threw their dust into the brook Kidron.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The high places which <i>were</i> before Jerusalem, which <i>were</i> on the right of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10179W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10179W\"></sup>the mount of destruction which Solomon the king of Israel had built for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10179X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10179X\"></sup>Ashtoreth the abomination of the Sidonians, and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10179Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10179Y\"></sup>Chemosh the abomination of Moab, and for Milcom the abomination of the sons of Ammon, the king defiled.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10180Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10180Z\"></sup>He broke in pieces the <i>sacred</i> pillars and cut down the Asherim and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10180AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10180AA\"></sup>filled their places with human bones.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Furthermore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10181AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10181AB\"></sup>the altar that <i>was</i> at Bethel <i>and</i> the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10181AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10181AC\"></sup>high place which Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who made Israel sin, had made, even that altar and the high place he broke down. Then he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10181AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10181AD\"></sup>demolished its stones, ground them to dust, and burned the Asherah.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now when Josiah turned, he saw the graves that <i>were</i> there on the mountain, and he sent and took the bones from the graves and burned <i>them</i> on the altar and defiled it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10182AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10182AE\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which the man of God proclaimed, who proclaimed these things.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then he said, “What is this monument that I see?” And the men of the city told him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10183AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10183AF\"></sup>It is the grave of the man of God who came from Judah and proclaimed these things which you have done against the altar of Bethel.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He said, “Let him alone; let no one disturb his bones.” So they left his bones undisturbed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10184AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10184AG\"></sup>with the bones of the prophet who came from Samaria.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Josiah also removed all the houses of the high places which <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10185AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10185AH\"></sup>in the cities of Samaria, which the kings of Israel had made provoking the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and he did to them just as he had done in Bethel.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>All the priests of the high places who <i>were</i> there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10186AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10186AI\"></sup>he slaughtered on the altars and burned human bones on them; then he returned to Jerusalem.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the king commanded all the people saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10187AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10187AJ\"></sup>Celebrate the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10187AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10187AK\"></sup>as it is written in this book of the covenant.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10188AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10188AL\"></sup>Surely such a Passover had not been celebrated from the days of the judges who judged Israel, nor in all the days of the kings of Israel and of the kings of Judah.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But in the eighteenth year of King Josiah, this Passover was observed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Moreover, Josiah removed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10190AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10190AM\"></sup>the mediums and the spiritists and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10190AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10190AN\"></sup>teraphim and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10190AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10190AO\"></sup>the idols and all the abominations that were seen in the land of Judah and in Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10190AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10190AP\"></sup>that he might confirm the words of the law which were written <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10190AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10190AQ\"></sup>in the book that Hilkiah the priest found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Before him there was no king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10191AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10191AR\"></sup>like him who turned to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all his heart and with all his soul and with all his might, according to all the law of Moses; nor did any like him arise after him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>However, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not turn from the fierceness of His great wrath with which His anger burned against Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10192AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10192AS\"></sup>because of all the provocations with which Manasseh had provoked Him.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “I will remove Judah also from My sight, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10193AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10193AT\"></sup>as I have removed Israel. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10193AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10193AU\"></sup>I will cast off Jerusalem, this city which I have chosen, and the temple of which I said, ‘My name shall be there.’”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Josiah and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10195AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10195AV\"></sup>In his days <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10195AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10195AW\"></sup>Pharaoh Neco king of Egypt went up to the king of Assyria to the river Euphrates. And King Josiah went to meet him, and when <i>Pharaoh Neco</i> saw him he killed him at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10195AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10195AX\"></sup>Megiddo.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10196AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10196AY\"></sup>His servants drove his body in a chariot from Megiddo, and brought him to Jerusalem and buried him in his own tomb. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10196AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10196AZ\"></sup>Then the people of the land took Jehoahaz the son of Josiah and anointed him and made him king in place of his father.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10197BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10197BA\"></sup>Jehoahaz was twenty-three years old when he became king, and he reigned three months in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10197BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10197BB\"></sup>Hamutal the daughter of Jeremiah of Libnah.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10198BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10198BC\"></sup>according to all that his fathers had done.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10199BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10199BD\"></sup>Pharaoh Neco imprisoned him at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10199BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10199BE\"></sup>Riblah in the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10199BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10199BF\"></sup>Hamath, that he might not reign in Jerusalem; and he imposed on the land a fine of one hundred talents of silver and a talent of gold.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Pharaoh Neco made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10200BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10200BG\"></sup>Eliakim the son of Josiah king in the place of Josiah his father, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10200BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10200BH\"></sup>changed his name to Jehoiakim. But he took Jehoahaz away and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10200BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10200BI\"></sup>brought <i>him</i> to Egypt, and he died there.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>So Jehoiakim <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10201BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10201BJ\"></sup>gave the silver and gold to Pharaoh, but he taxed the land in order to give the money at the command of Pharaoh. He exacted the silver and gold from the people of the land, each according to his valuation, to give it to Pharaoh Neco.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10202BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10202BK\"></sup>Jehoiakim was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name <i>was</i> Zebidah the daughter of Pedaiah of Rumah.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10203BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10203BL\"></sup>according to all that his fathers had done."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10204A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10204A\"></sup>In his days Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up, and Jehoiakim became his servant <i>for</i> three years; then he turned and rebelled against him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent against him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10205B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10205B\"></sup>bands of Chaldeans, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10205C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10205C\"></sup>bands of Arameans, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10205D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10205D\"></sup>bands of Moabites, and bands of Ammonites. So He sent them against Judah to destroy it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10205E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10205E\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which He had spoken through His servants the prophets.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10206F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10206F\"></sup>Surely at the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> it came upon Judah, to remove <i>them</i> from His sight <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10206G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10206G\"></sup>because of the sins of Manasseh, according to all that he had done,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10207H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10207H\"></sup>also for the innocent blood which he shed, for he filled Jerusalem with innocent blood; and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> would not forgive.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jehoiakim and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10209I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10209I\"></sup>Jehoiakim slept with his fathers, and Jehoiachin his son became king in his place.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10210J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10210J\"></sup>The king of Egypt did not come out of his land again, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10210K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10210K\"></sup>for the king of Babylon had taken all that belonged to the king of Egypt from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10210L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10210L\"></sup>the brook of Egypt to the river Euphrates.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10211M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10211M\"></sup>Jehoiachin was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10211N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10211N\"></sup>eighteen years old when he became king, and he reigned three months in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name <i>was</i> Nehushta the daughter of Elnathan of Jerusalem.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10212O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10212O\"></sup>according to all that his father had done.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>At that time the servants of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon went up to Jerusalem, and the city came under siege.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon came to the city, while his servants were besieging it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10215P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10215P\"></sup>Jehoiachin the king of Judah went out to the king of Babylon, he and his mother and his servants and his captains and his officials. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10215Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10215Q\"></sup>the king of Babylon took him captive in the eighth year of his reign.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10216R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10216R\"></sup>He carried out from there all the treasures of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the treasures of the king’s house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10216S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10216S\"></sup>cut in pieces all the vessels of gold <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10216T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10216T\"></sup>which Solomon king of Israel had made in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10217U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10217U\"></sup>he led away into exile all Jerusalem and all the captains and all the mighty men of valor, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10217V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10217V\"></sup>ten thousand captives, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10217W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10217W\"></sup>all the craftsmen and the smiths. None remained <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10217X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10217X\"></sup>except the poorest people of the land.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10218Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10218Y\"></sup>he led Jehoiachin away into exile to Babylon; also the king’s mother and the king’s wives and his officials and the leading men of the land, he led away into exile from Jerusalem to Babylon.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>All the men of valor, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10219Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10219Z\"></sup>seven thousand, and the craftsmen and the smiths, one thousand, all strong and fit for war, and these the king of Babylon brought into exile to Babylon.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10220AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10220AA\"></sup>Then the king of Babylon made his uncle Mattaniah king in his place, and changed his name to Zedekiah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10221AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10221AB\"></sup>Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem; and his mother’s name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10221AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10221AC\"></sup>Hamutal the daughter of Jeremiah of Libnah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He did evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10222AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10222AD\"></sup>according to all that Jehoiakim had done.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10223AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10223AE\"></sup>through the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>this</i> came about in Jerusalem and Judah until He cast them out from His presence. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10223AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10223AF\"></sup>Zedekiah rebelled against the king of Babylon."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10224A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10224A\"></sup>Now in the ninth year of his reign, on the tenth day of the tenth month, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10224B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10224B\"></sup>Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came, he and all his army, against Jerusalem, camped against it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10224C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10224C\"></sup>built a siege wall all around it.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the city was under siege until the eleventh year of King Zedekiah.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>On the ninth day of the <i>fourth</i> month <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10226D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10226D\"></sup>the famine was so severe in the city that there was no food for the people of the land.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10227E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10227E\"></sup>Then the city was broken into, and all the men of war <i>fled</i> by night by way of the gate between the two walls beside <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10227F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10227F\"></sup>the king’s garden, though the Chaldeans were all around the city. And they went by way of the Arabah.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But the army of the Chaldeans pursued the king and overtook him in the plains of Jericho and all his army was scattered from him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10229G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10229G\"></sup>they captured the king and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10229H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10229H\"></sup>brought him to the king of Babylon at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10229I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10229I\"></sup>Riblah, and he passed sentence on him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10230J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10230J\"></sup>They slaughtered the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10230K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10230K\"></sup>put out the eyes of Zedekiah and bound him with bronze fetters and brought him to Babylon.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10231L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10231L\"></sup>Now on the seventh day of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10231M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10231M\"></sup>fifth month, which was the nineteenth year of King Nebuchadnezzar, king of Babylon, Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard, a servant of the king of Babylon, came to Jerusalem.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10232N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10232N\"></sup>He burned the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10232O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10232O\"></sup>the king’s house, and all the houses of Jerusalem; even every great house he burned with fire.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So all the army of the Chaldeans who <i>were with</i> the captain of the guard <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10233P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10233P\"></sup>broke down the walls around Jerusalem.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10234Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10234Q\"></sup>the rest of the people who were left in the city and the deserters who had deserted to the king of Babylon and the rest of the people, Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard carried away into exile.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But the captain of the guard left some of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10235R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10235R\"></sup>the poorest of the land to be vinedressers and plowmen.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10236S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10236S\"></sup>Now the bronze pillars which were in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the stands and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10236T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10236T\"></sup>the bronze sea which were in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the Chaldeans broke in pieces and carried the bronze to Babylon.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10237U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10237U\"></sup>They took away the pots, the shovels, the snuffers, the spoons, and all the bronze vessels which were used in <i>temple</i> service.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The captain of the guard also took away the firepans and the basins, what was fine gold and what was fine silver.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The two pillars, the one sea, and the stands which Solomon had made for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10239V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10239V\"></sup>the bronze of all these vessels was beyond weight.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10240W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10240W\"></sup>The height of the one pillar was eighteen cubits, and a bronze capital was on it; the height of the capital was three cubits, with a network and pomegranates on the capital all around, all of bronze. And the second pillar was like these with network.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the captain of the guard took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10241X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10241X\"></sup>Seraiah the chief priest and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10241Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10241Y\"></sup>Zephaniah the second priest, with the three officers of the temple.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>From the city he took one official who was overseer of the men of war, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10242Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10242Z\"></sup>five of the king’s advisers who were found in the city; and the scribe of the captain of the army who mustered the people of the land; and sixty men of the people of the land who were found in the city.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard took them and brought them to the king of Babylon at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10243AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10243AA\"></sup>Riblah.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the king of Babylon struck them down and put them to death at Riblah in the land of Hamath. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10244AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10244AB\"></sup>So Judah was led away into exile from its land.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now <i>as for</i> the people who were left in the land of Judah, whom Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon had left, he appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10245AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10245AC\"></sup>Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan over them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10246AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10246AD\"></sup>When all the captains of the forces, they and <i>their</i> men, heard that the king of Babylon had appointed Gedaliah <i>governor</i>, they came to Gedaliah to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10246AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10246AE\"></sup>Mizpah, namely, Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, and Johanan the son of Kareah, and Seraiah the son of Tanhumeth the Netophathite, and Jaazaniah the son of the Maacathite, they and their men.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Gedaliah swore to them and their men and said to them, “Do not be afraid of the servants of the Chaldeans; live in the land and serve the king of Babylon, and it will be well with you.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10248AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10248AF\"></sup>But it came about in the seventh month, that Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, the son of Elishama, of the royal family, came with ten men and struck Gedaliah down so that he died along with the Jews and the Chaldeans who were with him at Mizpah.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10249AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10249AG\"></sup>Then all the people, both small and great, and the captains of the forces arose and went to Egypt; for they were afraid of the Chaldeans.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10250AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10250AH\"></sup>Now it came about in the thirty-seventh year of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10250AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10250AI\"></sup>the exile of Jehoiachin king of Judah, in the twelfth month, on the twenty-seventh <i>day</i> of the month, that Evil-merodach king of Babylon, in the year that he became king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10250AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10250AJ\"></sup>released Jehoiachin king of Judah from prison;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10251AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10251AK\"></sup>spoke kindly to him and set his throne above the throne of the kings who <i>were</i> with him in Babylon.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Jehoiachin changed his prison clothes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10252AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10252AL\"></sup>had his meals in the king’s presence regularly all the days of his life;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and for his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10253AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10253AM\"></sup>allowance, a regular allowance was given him by the king, a portion for each day, all the days of his life."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;